01Gn 12:9 Then Abram set out and continued toward the Negev.
01Gn 12:10 Now there was a famine in the land, and Abram went down to Egypt to live there for a while because the famine was severe.
01Gn 12:11 As he was about to enter Egypt, he said to his wife Sarai, "I know what a beautiful woman you are.
01Gn 12:12 When the Egyptians see you, they will say, 'This is his wife.' Then they will kill me but will let you live.
01Gn 12:13 Say you are my sister, so that I will be treated well for your sake and my life will be spared because of you."
01Gn 12:14 When Abram came to Egypt, the Egyptians saw that she was a very beautiful woman.
01Gn 12:15 And when Pharaoh's officials saw her, they praised her to Pharaoh, and she was taken into his palace.
01Gn 12:16 He treated Abram well for her sake, and Abram acquired sheep and cattle, male and female donkeys, menservants and maidservants, and camels.
01Gn 12:17 But the LORD inflicted serious diseases on Pharaoh and his household because of Abram's wife Sarai.
01Gn 12:18 So Pharaoh summoned Abram. "What have you done to me?" he said. "Why didn't you tell me she was your wife?
01Gn 12:19 Why did you say, 'She is my sister,' so that I took her to be my wife? Now then, here is your wife. Take her and go!"
01Gn 12:20 Then Pharaoh gave orders about Abram to his men, and they sent him on his way, with his wife and everything he had.
