01Gn 14:23 that I will accept nothing belonging to you, not even a thread or the thong of a sandal, so that you will never be able to say, 'I made Abram rich.'
01Gn 14:24 I will accept nothing but what my men have eaten and the share that belongs to the men who went with me--to Aner, Eshcol and Mamre. Let them have their share."
01Gn 15:1 After this, the word of the LORD came to Abram in a vision£º "Do not be afraid, Abram. I am your shield, your very great reward."
01Gn 15:2 But Abram said, "O Sovereign LORD, what can you give me since I remain childless and the one who will inherit my estate is Eliezer of Damascus?"
01Gn 15:3 And Abram said, "You have given me no children; so a servant in my household will be my heir."
01Gn 15:4 Then the word of the LORD came to him£º "This man will not be your heir, but a son coming from your own body will be your heir."
01Gn 15:5 He took him outside and said, "Look up at the heavens and count the stars--if indeed you can count them." Then he said to him, "So shall your offspring be."
01Gn 15:6 Abram believed the LORD, and he credited it to him as righteousness.
01Gn 15:7 He also said to him, "I am the LORD, who brought you out of Ur of the Chaldeans to give you this land to take possession of it."
01Gn 15:8 But Abram said, "O Sovereign LORD, how can I know that I will gain possession of it?"
01Gn 15:9 So the LORD said to him, "Bring me a heifer, a goat and a ram, each three years old, along with a dove and a young pigeon."
01Gn 15:10 Abram brought all these to him, cut them in two and arranged the halves opposite each other; the birds, however, he did not cut in half.
01Gn 15:11 Then birds of prey came down on the carcasses, but Abram drove them away.
01Gn 15:12 As the sun was setting, Abram fell into a deep sleep, and a thick and dreadful darkness came over him.
