01Gn 44:3 As morning dawned, the men were sent on their way with their donkeys.
01Gn 44:4 They had not gone far from the city when Joseph said to his steward, "Go after those men at once, and when you catch up with them, say to them, 'Why have you repaid good with evil?
01Gn 44:5 Isn't this the cup my master drinks from and also uses for divination? This is a wicked thing you have done.'"
01Gn 44:6 When he caught up with them, he repeated these words to them.
01Gn 44:7 But they said to him, "Why does my lord say such things? Far be it from your servants to do anything like that!
