02Ex 16:12 "I have heard the grumbling of the Israelites. Tell them, 'At twilight you will eat meat, and in the morning you will be filled with bread. Then you will know that I am the LORD your God.'"
02Ex 16:13 That evening quail came and covered the camp, and in the morning there was a layer of dew around the camp.
02Ex 16:14 When the dew was gone, thin flakes like frost on the ground appeared on the desert floor.
02Ex 16:15 When the Israelites saw it, they said to each other, "What is it?" For they did not know what it was. Moses said to them, "It is the bread the LORD has given you to eat.
02Ex 16:16 This is what the LORD has commanded£º 'Each one is to gather as much as he needs. Take an omer for each person you have in your tent.'"
02Ex 16:17 The Israelites did as they were told; some gathered much, some little.
02Ex 16:18 And when they measured it by the omer, he who gathered much did not have too much, and he who gathered little did not have too little. Each one gathered as much as he needed.
02Ex 16:19 Then Moses said to them, "No one is to keep any of it until morning."
02Ex 16:20 However, some of them paid no attention to Moses; they kept part of it until morning, but it was full of maggots and began to smell. So Moses was angry with them.
02Ex 16:21 Each morning everyone gathered as much as he needed, and when the sun grew hot, it melted away.
02Ex 16:22 On the sixth day, they gathered twice as much--two omers for each person--and the leaders of the community came and reported this to Moses.
02Ex 16:23 He said to them, "This is what the LORD commanded£º 'Tomorrow is to be a day of rest, a holy Sabbath to the LORD. So bake what you want to bake and boil what you want to boil. Save whatever is left and keep it until morning.'"
