02Ex 24:3 When Moses went and told the people all the LORD'S words and laws, they responded with one voice, "Everything the LORD has said we will do."
02Ex 24:4 Moses then wrote down everything the LORD had said. He got up early the next morning and built an altar at the foot of the mountain and set up twelve stone pillars representing the twelve tribes of Israel.
02Ex 24:5 Then he sent young Israelite men, and they offered burnt offerings and sacrificed young bulls as fellowship offerings to the LORD.
02Ex 24:6 Moses took half of the blood and put it in bowls, and the other half he sprinkled on the altar.
02Ex 24:7 Then he took the Book of the Covenant and read it to the people. They responded, "We will do everything the LORD has said; we will obey."
02Ex 24:8 Moses then took the blood, sprinkled it on the people and said, "This is the blood of the covenant that the LORD has made with you in accordance with all these words."
02Ex 24:9 Moses and Aaron, Nadab and Abihu, and the seventy elders of Israel went up
02Ex 24:10 and saw the God of Israel. Under his feet was something like a pavement made of sapphire, clear as the sky itself.
02Ex 24:11 But God did not raise his hand against these leaders of the Israelites; they saw God, and they ate and drank.
02Ex 24:12 The LORD said to Moses, "Come up to me on the mountain and stay here, and I will give you the tablets of stone, with the law and commands I have written for their instruction."
02Ex 24:13 Then Moses set out with Joshua his aide, and Moses went up on the mountain of God.
02Ex 24:14 He said to the elders, "Wait here for us until we come back to you. Aaron and Hur are with you, and anyone involved in a dispute can go to them."
02Ex 24:15 When Moses went up on the mountain, the cloud covered it,
02Ex 24:16 and the glory of the LORD settled on Mount Sinai. For six days the cloud covered the mountain, and on the seventh day the LORD called to Moses from within the cloud.
02Ex 24:17 To the Israelites the glory of the LORD looked like a consuming fire on top of the mountain.
02Ex 24:18 Then Moses entered the cloud as he went on up the mountain. And he stayed on the mountain forty days and forty nights.
02Ex 25:1 The LORD said to Moses,
02Ex 25:2 "Tell the Israelites to bring me an offering. You are to receive the offering for me from each man whose heart prompts him to give.
02Ex 25:3 These are the offerings you are to receive from them£º gold, silver and bronze;
02Ex 25:4 blue, purple and scarlet yarn and fine linen; goat hair;
02Ex 25:5 ram skins dyed red and hides of sea cows; acacia wood;
02Ex 25:6 olive oil for the light; spices for the anointing oil and for the fragrant incense;
02Ex 25:7 and onyx stones and other gems to be mounted on the ephod and breastpiece.
02Ex 25:8 "Then have them make a sanctuary for me, and I will dwell among them.
02Ex 25:9 Make this tabernacle and all its furnishings exactly like the pattern I will show you.
02Ex 25:10 "Have them make a chest of acacia wood--two and a half cubits long, a cubit and a half wide, and a cubit and a half high.
02Ex 25:11 Overlay it with pure gold, both inside and out, and make a gold molding around it.
02Ex 25:12 Cast four gold rings for it and fasten them to its four feet, with two rings on one side and two rings on the other.
02Ex 25:13 Then make poles of acacia wood and overlay them with gold.
02Ex 25:14 Insert the poles into the rings on the sides of the chest to carry it.
02Ex 25:15 The poles are to remain in the rings of this ark; they are not to be removed.
02Ex 25:16 Then put in the ark the Testimony, which I will give you.
02Ex 25:17 "Make an atonement cover of pure gold--two and a half cubits long and a cubit and a half wide.
02Ex 25:18 And make two cherubim out of hammered gold at the ends of the cover.
02Ex 25:19 Make one cherub on one end and the second cherub on the other; make the cherubim of one piece with the cover, at the two ends.
02Ex 25:20 The cherubim are to have their wings spread upward, overshadowing the cover with them. The cherubim are to face each other, looking toward the cover.
02Ex 25:21 Place the cover on top of the ark and put in the ark the Testimony, which I will give you.
02Ex 25:22 There, above the cover between the two cherubim that are over the ark of the Testimony, I will meet with you and give you all my commands for the Israelites.
02Ex 25:23 "Make a table of acacia wood--two cubits long, a cubit wide and a cubit and a half high.
02Ex 25:24 Overlay it with pure gold and make a gold molding around it.
02Ex 25:25 Also make around it a rim a handbreadth wide and put a gold molding on the rim.
02Ex 25:26 Make four gold rings for the table and fasten them to the four corners, where the four legs are.
02Ex 25:27 The rings are to be close to the rim to hold the poles used in carrying the table.
02Ex 25:28 Make the poles of acacia wood, overlay them with gold and carry the table with them.
02Ex 25:29 And make its plates and dishes of pure gold, as well as its pitchers and bowls for the pouring out of offerings.
02Ex 25:30 Put the bread of the Presence on this table to be before me at all times.
02Ex 25:31 "Make a lampstand of pure gold and hammer it out, base and shaft; its flowerlike cups, buds and blossoms shall be of one piece with it.
02Ex 25:32 Six branches are to extend from the sides of the lampstand--three on one side and three on the other.
02Ex 25:33 Three cups shaped like almond flowers with buds and blossoms are to be on one branch, three on the next branch, and the same for all six branches extending from the lampstand.
02Ex 25:34 And on the lampstand there are to be four cups shaped like almond flowers with buds and blossoms.
02Ex 25:35 One bud shall be under the first pair of branches extending from the lampstand, a second bud under the second pair, and a third bud under the third pair--six branches in all.
02Ex 25:36 The buds and branches shall all be of one piece with the lampstand, hammered out of pure gold.
02Ex 25:37 "Then make its seven lamps and set them up on it so that they light the space in front of it.
02Ex 25:38 Its wick trimmers and trays are to be of pure gold.
02Ex 25:39 A talent of pure gold is to be used for the lampstand and all these accessories.
02Ex 25:40 See that you make them according to the pattern shown you on the mountain.
02Ex 26:1 "Make the tabernacle with ten curtains of finely twisted linen and blue, purple and scarlet yarn, with cherubim worked into them by a skilled craftsman.
02Ex 26:2 All the curtains are to be the same size--twenty-eight cubits long and four cubits wide.
02Ex 26:3 Join five of the curtains together, and do the same with the other five.
02Ex 26:4 Make loops of blue material along the edge of the end curtain in one set, and do the same with the end curtain in the other set.
02Ex 26:5 Make fifty loops on one curtain and fifty loops on the end curtain of the other set, with the loops opposite each other.
02Ex 26:6 Then make fifty gold clasps and use them to fasten the curtains together so that the tabernacle is a unit.
02Ex 26:7 "Make curtains of goat hair for the tent over the tabernacle--eleven altogether.
02Ex 26:8 All eleven curtains are to be the same size--thirty cubits long and four cubits wide.
02Ex 26:9 Join five of the curtains together into one set and the other six into another set. Fold the sixth curtain double at the front of the tent.
02Ex 26:10 Make fifty loops along the edge of the end curtain in one set and also along the edge of the end curtain in the other set.
02Ex 26:11 Then make fifty bronze clasps and put them in the loops to fasten the tent together as a unit.
02Ex 26:12 As for the additional length of the tent curtains, the half curtain that is left over is to hang down at the rear of the tabernacle.
02Ex 26:13 The tent curtains will be a cubit longer on both sides; what is left will hang over the sides of the tabernacle so as to cover it.
02Ex 26:14 Make for the tent a covering of ram skins dyed red, and over that a covering of hides of sea cows.
02Ex 26:15 "Make upright frames of acacia wood for the tabernacle.
02Ex 26:16 Each frame is to be ten cubits long and a cubit and a half wide,
02Ex 26:17 with two projections set parallel to each other. Make all the frames of the tabernacle in this way.
02Ex 26:18 Make twenty frames for the south side of the tabernacle
02Ex 26:19 and make forty silver bases to go under them--two bases for each frame, one under each projection.
02Ex 26:20 For the other side, the north side of the tabernacle, make twenty frames
02Ex 26:21 and forty silver bases--two under each frame.
02Ex 26:22 Make six frames for the far end, that is, the west end of the tabernacle,
02Ex 26:23 and make two frames for the corners at the far end.
02Ex 26:24 At these two corners they must be double from the bottom all the way to the top, and fitted into a single ring; both shall be like that.
02Ex 26:25 So there will be eight frames and sixteen silver bases--two under each frame.
02Ex 26:26 "Also make crossbars of acacia wood£º five for the frames on one side of the tabernacle,
02Ex 26:27 five for those on the other side, and five for the frames on the west, at the far end of the tabernacle.
02Ex 26:28 The center crossbar is to extend from end to end at the middle of the frames.
02Ex 26:29 Overlay the frames with gold and make gold rings to hold the crossbars. Also overlay the crossbars with gold.
02Ex 26:30 "Set up the tabernacle according to the plan shown you on the mountain.
02Ex 26:31 "Make a curtain of blue, purple and scarlet yarn and finely twisted linen, with cherubim worked into it by a skilled craftsman.
02Ex 26:32 Hang it with gold hooks on four posts of acacia wood overlaid with gold and standing on four silver bases.
02Ex 26:33 Hang the curtain from the clasps and place the ark of the Testimony behind the curtain. The curtain will separate the Holy Place from the Most Holy Place.
02Ex 26:34 Put the atonement cover on the ark of the Testimony in the Most Holy Place.
02Ex 26:35 Place the table outside the curtain on the north side of the tabernacle and put the lampstand opposite it on the south side.
02Ex 26:36 "For the entrance to the tent make a curtain of blue, purple and scarlet yarn and finely twisted linen--the work of an embroiderer.
02Ex 26:37 Make gold hooks for this curtain and five posts of acacia wood overlaid with gold. And cast five bronze bases for them.
02Ex 27:1 "Build an altar of acacia wood, three cubits high; it is to be square, five cubits long and five cubits wide.
02Ex 27:2 Make a horn at each of the four corners, so that the horns and the altar are of one piece, and overlay the altar with bronze.
02Ex 27:3 Make all its utensils of bronze--its pots to remove the ashes, and its shovels, sprinkling bowls, meat forks and firepans.
02Ex 27:4 Make a grating for it, a bronze network, and make a bronze ring at each of the four corners of the network.
02Ex 27:5 Put it under the ledge of the altar so that it is halfway up the altar.
02Ex 27:6 Make poles of acacia wood for the altar and overlay them with bronze.
02Ex 27:7 The poles are to be inserted into the rings so they will be on two sides of the altar when it is carried.
02Ex 27:8 Make the altar hollow, out of boards. It is to be made just as you were shown on the mountain.
02Ex 27:9 "Make a courtyard for the tabernacle. The south side shall be a hundred cubits long and is to have curtains of finely twisted linen,
02Ex 27:10 with twenty posts and twenty bronze bases and with silver hooks and bands on the posts.
02Ex 27:11 The north side shall also be a hundred cubits long and is to have curtains, with twenty posts and twenty bronze bases and with silver hooks and bands on the posts.
02Ex 27:12 "The west end of the courtyard shall be fifty cubits wide and have curtains, with ten posts and ten bases.
02Ex 27:13 On the east end, toward the sunrise, the courtyard shall also be fifty cubits wide.
02Ex 27:14 Curtains fifteen cubits long are to be on one side of the entrance, with three posts and three bases,
02Ex 27:15 and curtains fifteen cubits long are to be on the other side, with three posts and three bases.
02Ex 27:16 "For the entrance to the courtyard, provide a curtain twenty cubits long, of blue, purple and scarlet yarn and finely twisted linen--the work of an embroiderer--with four posts and four bases.
02Ex 27:17 All the posts around the courtyard are to have silver bands and hooks, and bronze bases.
02Ex 27:18 The courtyard shall be a hundred cubits long and fifty cubits wide, with curtains of finely twisted linen five cubits high, and with bronze bases.
02Ex 27:19 All the other articles used in the service of the tabernacle, whatever their function, including all the tent pegs for it and those for the courtyard, are to be of bronze.
02Ex 27:20 "Command the Israelites to bring you clear oil of pressed olives for the light so that the lamps may be kept burning.
02Ex 27:21 In the Tent of Meeting, outside the curtain that is in front of the Testimony, Aaron and his sons are to keep the lamps burning before the LORD from evening till morning. This is to be a lasting ordinance among the Israelites for the generations to come.
02Ex 28:1 "Have Aaron your brother brought to you from among the Israelites, along with his sons Nadab and Abihu, Eleazar and Ithamar, so they may serve me as priests.
02Ex 28:2 Make sacred garments for your brother Aaron, to give him dignity and honor.
02Ex 28:3 Tell all the skilled men to whom I have given wisdom in such matters that they are to make garments for Aaron, for his consecration, so he may serve me as priest.
02Ex 28:4 These are the garments they are to make£º a breastpiece, an ephod, a robe, a woven tunic, a turban and a sash. They are to make these sacred garments for your brother Aaron and his sons, so they may serve me as priests.
02Ex 28:5 Have them use gold, and blue, purple and scarlet yarn, and fine linen.
02Ex 28:6 "Make the ephod of gold, and of blue, purple and scarlet yarn, and of finely twisted linen--the work of a skilled craftsman.
02Ex 28:7 It is to have two shoulder pieces attached to two of its corners, so it can be fastened.
02Ex 28:8 Its skillfully woven waistband is to be like it--of one piece with the ephod and made with gold, and with blue, purple and scarlet yarn, and with finely twisted linen.
02Ex 28:9 "Take two onyx stones and engrave on them the names of the sons of Israel
02Ex 28:10 in the order of their birth--six names on one stone and the remaining six on the other.
02Ex 28:11 Engrave the names of the sons of Israel on the two stones the way a gem cutter engraves a seal. Then mount the stones in gold filigree settings
02Ex 28:12 and fasten them on the shoulder pieces of the ephod as memorial stones for the sons of Israel. Aaron is to bear the names on his shoulders as a memorial before the LORD.
02Ex 28:13 Make gold filigree settings
02Ex 28:14 and two braided chains of pure gold, like a rope, and attach the chains to the settings.
02Ex 28:15 "Fashion a breastpiece for making decisions--the work of a skilled craftsman. Make it like the ephod£º of gold, and of blue, purple and scarlet yarn, and of finely twisted linen.
02Ex 28:16 It is to be square--a span long and a span wide--and folded double.
02Ex 28:17 Then mount four rows of precious stones on it. In the first row there shall be a ruby, a topaz and a beryl;
02Ex 28:18 in the second row a turquoise, a sapphire and an emerald;
02Ex 28:19 in the third row a jacinth, an agate and an amethyst;
02Ex 28:20 in the fourth row a chrysolite, an onyx and a jasper. Mount them in gold filigree settings.
02Ex 28:21 There are to be twelve stones, one for each of the names of the sons of Israel, each engraved like a seal with the name of one of the twelve tribes.
02Ex 28:22 "For the breastpiece make braided chains of pure gold, like a rope.
02Ex 28:23 Make two gold rings for it and fasten them to two corners of the breastpiece.
02Ex 28:24 Fasten the two gold chains to the rings at the corners of the breastpiece,
02Ex 28:25 and the other ends of the chains to the two settings, attaching them to the shoulder pieces of the ephod at the front.
02Ex 28:26 Make two gold rings and attach them to the other two corners of the breastpiece on the inside edge next to the ephod.
02Ex 28:27 Make two more gold rings and attach them to the bottom of the shoulder pieces on the front of the ephod, close to the seam just above the waistband of the ephod.
02Ex 28:28 The rings of the breastpiece are to be tied to the rings of the ephod with blue cord, connecting it to the waistband, so that the breastpiece will not swing out from the ephod.
02Ex 28:29 "Whenever Aaron enters the Holy Place, he will bear the names of the sons of Israel over his heart on the breastpiece of decision as a continuing memorial before the LORD.
02Ex 28:30 Also put the Urim and the Thummim in the breastpiece, so they may be over Aaron's heart whenever he enters the presence of the LORD. Thus Aaron will always bear the means of making decisions for the Israelites over his heart before the LORD.
02Ex 28:31 "Make the robe of the ephod entirely of blue cloth,
02Ex 28:32 with an opening for the head in its center. There shall be a woven edge like a collar around this opening, so that it will not tear.
02Ex 28:33 Make pomegranates of blue, purple and scarlet yarn around the hem of the robe, with gold bells between them.
02Ex 28:34 The gold bells and the pomegranates are to alternate around the hem of the robe.
02Ex 28:35 Aaron must wear it when he ministers. The sound of the bells will be heard when he enters the Holy Place before the LORD and when he comes out, so that he will not die.
02Ex 28:36 "Make a plate of pure gold and engrave on it as on a seal£º HOLY TO THE LORD.
02Ex 28:37 Fasten a blue cord to it to attach it to the turban; it is to be on the front of the turban.
02Ex 28:38 It will be on Aaron's forehead, and he will bear the guilt involved in the sacred gifts the Israelites consecrate, whatever their gifts may be. It will be on Aaron's forehead continually so that they will be acceptable to the LORD.
02Ex 28:39 "Weave the tunic of fine linen and make the turban of fine linen. The sash is to be the work of an embroiderer.
02Ex 28:40 Make tunics, sashes and headbands for Aaron's sons, to give them dignity and honor.
02Ex 28:41 After you put these clothes on your brother Aaron and his sons, anoint and ordain them. Consecrate them so they may serve me as priests.
02Ex 28:42 "Make linen undergarments as a covering for the body, reaching from the waist to the thigh.
02Ex 28:43 Aaron and his sons must wear them whenever they enter the Tent of Meeting or approach the altar to minister in the Holy Place, so that they will not incur guilt and die. "This is to be a lasting ordinance for Aaron and his descendants.
02Ex 29:1 "This is what you are to do to consecrate them, so they may serve me as priests£º Take a young bull and two rams without defect.
02Ex 29:2 And from fine wheat flour, without yeast, make bread, and cakes mixed with oil, and wafers spread with oil.
02Ex 29:3 Put them in a basket and present them in it--along with the bull and the two rams.
02Ex 29:4 Then bring Aaron and his sons to the entrance to the Tent of Meeting and wash them with water.
02Ex 29:5 Take the garments and dress Aaron with the tunic, the robe of the ephod, the ephod itself and the breastpiece. Fasten the ephod on him by its skillfully woven waistband.
02Ex 29:6 Put the turban on his head and attach the sacred diadem to the turban.
02Ex 29:7 Take the anointing oil and anoint him by pouring it on his head.
02Ex 29:8 Bring his sons and dress them in tunics
02Ex 29:9 and put headbands on them. Then tie sashes on Aaron and his sons. The priesthood is theirs by a lasting ordinance. In this way you shall ordain Aaron and his sons.
02Ex 29:10 "Bring the bull to the front of the Tent of Meeting, and Aaron and his sons shall lay their hands on its head.
02Ex 29:11 Slaughter it in the LORD'S presence at the entrance to the Tent of Meeting.
02Ex 29:12 Take some of the bull's blood and put it on the horns of the altar with your finger, and pour out the rest of it at the base of the altar.
02Ex 29:13 Then take all the fat around the inner parts, the covering of the liver, and both kidneys with the fat on them, and burn them on the altar.
02Ex 29:14 But burn the bull's flesh and its hide and its offal outside the camp. It is a sin offering.
02Ex 29:15 "Take one of the rams, and Aaron and his sons shall lay their hands on its head.
02Ex 29:16 Slaughter it and take the blood and sprinkle it against the altar on all sides.
02Ex 29:17 Cut the ram into pieces and wash the inner parts and the legs, putting them with the head and the other pieces.
02Ex 29:18 Then burn the entire ram on the altar. It is a burnt offering to the LORD, a pleasing aroma, an offering made to the LORD by fire.
02Ex 29:19 "Take the other ram, and Aaron and his sons shall lay their hands on its head.
02Ex 29:20 Slaughter it, take some of its blood and put it on the lobes of the right ears of Aaron and his sons, on the thumbs of their right hands, and on the big toes of their right feet. Then sprinkle blood against the altar on all sides.
02Ex 29:21 And take some of the blood on the altar and some of the anointing oil and sprinkle it on Aaron and his garments and on his sons and their garments. Then he and his sons and their garments will be consecrated.
02Ex 29:22 "Take from this ram the fat, the fat tail, the fat around the inner parts, the covering of the liver, both kidneys with the fat on them, and the right thigh. (This is the ram for the ordination.)
02Ex 29:23 From the basket of bread made without yeast, which is before the LORD, take a loaf, and a cake made with oil, and a wafer.
02Ex 29:24 Put all these in the hands of Aaron and his sons and wave them before the LORD as a wave offering.
02Ex 29:25 Then take them from their hands and burn them on the altar along with the burnt offering for a pleasing aroma to the LORD, an offering made to the LORD by fire.
02Ex 29:26 After you take the breast of the ram for Aaron's ordination, wave it before the LORD as a wave offering, and it will be your share.
02Ex 29:27 "Consecrate those parts of the ordination ram that belong to Aaron and his sons£º the breast that was waved and the thigh that was presented.
02Ex 29:28 This is always to be the regular share from the Israelites for Aaron and his sons. It is the contribution the Israelites are to make to the LORD from their fellowship offerings.
02Ex 29:29 "Aaron's sacred garments will belong to his descendants so that they can be anointed and ordained in them.
02Ex 29:30 The son who succeeds him as priest and comes to the Tent of Meeting to minister in the Holy Place is to wear them seven days.
02Ex 29:31 "Take the ram for the ordination and cook the meat in a sacred place.
02Ex 29:32 At the entrance to the Tent of Meeting, Aaron and his sons are to eat the meat of the ram and the bread that is in the basket.
02Ex 29:33 They are to eat these offerings by which atonement was made for their ordination and consecration. But no one else may eat them, because they are sacred.
02Ex 29:34 And if any of the meat of the ordination ram or any bread is left over till morning, burn it up. It must not be eaten, because it is sacred.
02Ex 29:35 "Do for Aaron and his sons everything I have commanded you, taking seven days to ordain them.
02Ex 29:36 Sacrifice a bull each day as a sin offering to make atonement. Purify the altar by making atonement for it, and anoint it to consecrate it.
02Ex 29:37 For seven days make atonement for the altar and consecrate it. Then the altar will be most holy, and whatever touches it will be holy.
02Ex 29:38 "This is what you are to offer on the altar regularly each day£º two lambs a year old.
02Ex 29:39 Offer one in the morning and the other at twilight.
02Ex 29:40 With the first lamb offer a tenth of an ephah of fine flour mixed with a quarter of a hin of oil from pressed olives, and a quarter of a hin of wine as a drink offering.
02Ex 29:41 Sacrifice the other lamb at twilight with the same grain offering and its drink offering as in the morning--a pleasing aroma, an offering made to the LORD by fire.
02Ex 29:42 "For the generations to come this burnt offering is to be made regularly at the entrance to the Tent of Meeting before the LORD. There I will meet you and speak to you;
02Ex 29:43 there also I will meet with the Israelites, and the place will be consecrated by my glory.
02Ex 29:44 "So I will consecrate the Tent of Meeting and the altar and will consecrate Aaron and his sons to serve me as priests.
02Ex 29:45 Then I will dwell among the Israelites and be their God.
02Ex 29:46 They will know that I am the LORD their God, who brought them out of Egypt so that I might dwell among them. I am the LORD their God.
02Ex 30:1 "Make an altar of acacia wood for burning incense.
02Ex 30:2 It is to be square, a cubit long and a cubit wide, and two cubits high--its horns of one piece with it.
02Ex 30:3 Overlay the top and all the sides and the horns with pure gold, and make a gold molding around it.
02Ex 30:4 Make two gold rings for the altar below the molding--two on opposite sides--to hold the poles used to carry it.
02Ex 30:5 Make the poles of acacia wood and overlay them with gold.
02Ex 30:6 Put the altar in front of the curtain that is before the ark of the Testimony--before the atonement cover that is over the Testimony--where I will meet with you.
02Ex 30:7 "Aaron must burn fragrant incense on the altar every morning when he tends the lamps.
02Ex 30:8 He must burn incense again when he lights the lamps at twilight so incense will burn regularly before the LORD for the generations to come.
02Ex 30:9 Do not offer on this altar any other incense or any burnt offering or grain offering, and do not pour a drink offering on it.
02Ex 30:10 Once a year Aaron shall make atonement on its horns. This annual atonement must be made with the blood of the atoning sin offering for the generations to come. It is most holy to the LORD."
02Ex 30:11 Then the LORD said to Moses,
02Ex 30:12 "When you take a census of the Israelites to count them, each one must pay the LORD a ransom for his life at the time he is counted. Then no plague will come on them when you number them.
02Ex 30:13 Each one who crosses over to those already counted is to give a half shekel, according to the sanctuary shekel, which weighs twenty gerahs. This half shekel is an offering to the LORD.
02Ex 30:14 All who cross over, those twenty years old or more, are to give an offering to the LORD.
02Ex 30:15 The rich are not to give more than a half shekel and the poor are not to give less when you make the offering to the LORD to atone for your lives.
02Ex 30:16 Receive the atonement money from the Israelites and use it for the service of the Tent of Meeting. It will be a memorial for the Israelites before the LORD, making atonement for your lives."
02Ex 30:17 Then the LORD said to Moses,
02Ex 30:18 "Make a bronze basin, with its bronze stand, for washing. Place it between the Tent of Meeting and the altar, and put water in it.
02Ex 30:19 Aaron and his sons are to wash their hands and feet with water from it.
02Ex 30:20 Whenever they enter the Tent of Meeting, they shall wash with water so that they will not die. Also, when they approach the altar to minister by presenting an offering made to the LORD by fire,
02Ex 30:21 they shall wash their hands and feet so that they will not die. This is to be a lasting ordinance for Aaron and his descendants for the generations to come."
02Ex 30:22 Then the LORD said to Moses,
02Ex 30:23 "Take the following fine spices£º 500 shekels of liquid myrrh, half as much (that is, 250 shekels) of fragrant cinnamon, 250 shekels of fragrant cane,
02Ex 30:24 500 shekels of cassia--all according to the sanctuary shekel--and a hin of olive oil.
02Ex 30:25 Make these into a sacred anointing oil, a fragrant blend, the work of a perfumer. It will be the sacred anointing oil.
02Ex 30:26 Then use it to anoint the Tent of Meeting, the ark of the Testimony,
02Ex 30:27 the table and all its articles, the lampstand and its accessories, the altar of incense,
02Ex 30:28 the altar of burnt offering and all its utensils, and the basin with its stand.
02Ex 30:29 You shall consecrate them so they will be most holy, and whatever touches them will be holy.
02Ex 30:30 "Anoint Aaron and his sons and consecrate them so they may serve me as priests.
02Ex 30:31 Say to the Israelites, 'This is to be my sacred anointing oil for the generations to come.
02Ex 30:32 Do not pour it on men's bodies and do not make any oil with the same formula. It is sacred, and you are to consider it sacred.
02Ex 30:33 Whoever makes perfume like it and whoever puts it on anyone other than a priest must be cut off from his people.'"
02Ex 30:34 Then the LORD said to Moses, "Take fragrant spices--gum resin, onycha and galbanum--and pure frankincense, all in equal amounts,
02Ex 30:35 and make a fragrant blend of incense, the work of a perfumer. It is to be salted and pure and sacred.
02Ex 30:36 Grind some of it to powder and place it in front of the Testimony in the Tent of Meeting, where I will meet with you. It shall be most holy to you.
02Ex 30:37 Do not make any incense with this formula for yourselves; consider it holy to the LORD.
02Ex 30:38 Whoever makes any like it to enjoy its fragrance must be cut off from his people."
02Ex 31:1 Then the LORD said to Moses,
02Ex 31:2 "See, I have chosen Bezalel son of Uri, the son of Hur, of the tribe of Judah,
02Ex 31:3 and I have filled him with the Spirit of God, with skill, ability and knowledge in all kinds of crafts--
02Ex 31:4 to make artistic designs for work in gold, silver and bronze,
02Ex 31:5 to cut and set stones, to work in wood, and to engage in all kinds of craftsmanship.
