02Ex 39:1 From the blue, purple and scarlet yarn they made woven garments for ministering in the sanctuary. They also made sacred garments for Aaron, as the LORD commanded Moses.
02Ex 39:2 They made the ephod of gold, and of blue, purple and scarlet yarn, and of finely twisted linen.
02Ex 39:3 They hammered out thin sheets of gold and cut strands to be worked into the blue, purple and scarlet yarn and fine linen--the work of a skilled craftsman.
02Ex 39:4 They made shoulder pieces for the ephod, which were attached to two of its corners, so it could be fastened.
02Ex 39:5 Its skillfully woven waistband was like it--of one piece with the ephod and made with gold, and with blue, purple and scarlet yarn, and with finely twisted linen, as the LORD commanded Moses.
02Ex 39:6 They mounted the onyx stones in gold filigree settings and engraved them like a seal with the names of the sons of Israel.
02Ex 39:7 Then they fastened them on the shoulder pieces of the ephod as memorial stones for the sons of Israel, as the LORD commanded Moses.
02Ex 39:8 They fashioned the breastpiece--the work of a skilled craftsman. They made it like the ephod£º of gold, and of blue, purple and scarlet yarn, and of finely twisted linen.
02Ex 39:9 It was square--a span long and a span wide--and folded double.
02Ex 39:10 Then they mounted four rows of precious stones on it. In the first row there was a ruby, a topaz and a beryl;
02Ex 39:11 in the second row a turquoise, a sapphire and an emerald;
02Ex 39:12 in the third row a jacinth, an agate and an amethyst;
02Ex 39:13 in the fourth row a chrysolite, an onyx and a jasper. They were mounted in gold filigree settings.
02Ex 39:14 There were twelve stones, one for each of the names of the sons of Israel, each engraved like a seal with the name of one of the twelve tribes.
02Ex 39:15 For the breastpiece they made braided chains of pure gold, like a rope.
02Ex 39:16 They made two gold filigree settings and two gold rings, and fastened the rings to two of the corners of the breastpiece.
02Ex 39:17 They fastened the two gold chains to the rings at the corners of the breastpiece,
02Ex 39:18 and the other ends of the chains to the two settings, attaching them to the shoulder pieces of the ephod at the front.
02Ex 39:19 They made two gold rings and attached them to the other two corners of the breastpiece on the inside edge next to the ephod.
02Ex 39:20 Then they made two more gold rings and attached them to the bottom of the shoulder pieces on the front of the ephod, close to the seam just above the waistband of the ephod.
02Ex 39:21 They tied the rings of the breastpiece to the rings of the ephod with blue cord, connecting it to the waistband so that the breastpiece would not swing out from the ephod--as the LORD commanded Moses.
02Ex 39:22 They made the robe of the ephod entirely of blue cloth--the work of a weaver--
02Ex 39:23 with an opening in the center of the robe like the opening of a collar, and a band around this opening, so that it would not tear.
02Ex 39:24 They made pomegranates of blue, purple and scarlet yarn and finely twisted linen around the hem of the robe.
02Ex 39:25 And they made bells of pure gold and attached them around the hem between the pomegranates.
02Ex 39:26 The bells and pomegranates alternated around the hem of the robe to be worn for ministering, as the LORD commanded Moses.
02Ex 39:27 For Aaron and his sons, they made tunics of fine linen--the work of a weaver--
02Ex 39:28 and the turban of fine linen, the linen headbands and the undergarments of finely twisted linen.
02Ex 39:29 The sash was of finely twisted linen and blue, purple and scarlet yarn--the work of an embroiderer--as the LORD commanded Moses.
02Ex 39:30 They made the plate, the sacred diadem, out of pure gold and engraved on it, like an inscription on a seal£º HOLY TO THE LORD.
02Ex 39:31 Then they fastened a blue cord to it to attach it to the turban, as the LORD commanded Moses.
02Ex 39:32 So all the work on the tabernacle, the Tent of Meeting, was completed. The Israelites did everything just as the LORD commanded Moses.
02Ex 39:33 Then they brought the tabernacle to Moses£º the tent and all its furnishings, its clasps, frames, crossbars, posts and bases;
02Ex 39:34 the covering of ram skins dyed red, the covering of hides of sea cows and the shielding curtain;
02Ex 39:35 the ark of the Testimony with its poles and the atonement cover;
02Ex 39:36 the table with all its articles and the bread of the Presence;
02Ex 39:37 the pure gold lampstand with its row of lamps and all its accessories, and the oil for the light;
02Ex 39:38 the gold altar, the anointing oil, the fragrant incense, and the curtain for the entrance to the tent;
02Ex 39:39 the bronze altar with its bronze grating, its poles and all its utensils; the basin with its stand;
02Ex 39:40 the curtains of the courtyard with its posts and bases, and the curtain for the entrance to the courtyard; the ropes and tent pegs for the courtyard; all the furnishings for the tabernacle, the Tent of Meeting;
02Ex 39:41 and the woven garments worn for ministering in the sanctuary, both the sacred garments for Aaron the priest and the garments for his sons when serving as priests.
02Ex 39:42 The Israelites had done all the work just as the LORD had commanded Moses.
02Ex 39:43 Moses inspected the work and saw that they had done it just as the LORD had commanded. So Moses blessed them.
02Ex 40:1 Then the LORD said to Moses£º
02Ex 40:2 "Set up the tabernacle, the Tent of Meeting, on the first day of the first month.
02Ex 40:3 Place the ark of the Testimony in it and shield the ark with the curtain.
02Ex 40:4 Bring in the table and set out what belongs on it. Then bring in the lampstand and set up its lamps.
