02Ex 40:25 and set up the lamps before the LORD, as the LORD commanded him.
02Ex 40:26 Moses placed the gold altar in the Tent of Meeting in front of the curtain
02Ex 40:27 and burned fragrant incense on it, as the LORD commanded him.
02Ex 40:28 Then he put up the curtain at the entrance to the tabernacle.
02Ex 40:29 He set the altar of burnt offering near the entrance to the tabernacle, the Tent of Meeting, and offered on it burnt offerings and grain offerings, as the LORD commanded him.
02Ex 40:30 He placed the basin between the Tent of Meeting and the altar and put water in it for washing,
02Ex 40:31 and Moses and Aaron and his sons used it to wash their hands and feet.
02Ex 40:32 They washed whenever they entered the Tent of Meeting or approached the altar, as the LORD commanded Moses.
02Ex 40:33 Then Moses set up the courtyard around the tabernacle and altar and put up the curtain at the entrance to the courtyard. And so Moses finished the work.
02Ex 40:34 Then the cloud covered the Tent of Meeting, and the glory of the LORD filled the tabernacle.
02Ex 40:35 Moses could not enter the Tent of Meeting because the cloud had settled upon it, and the glory of the LORD filled the tabernacle.
