04Nm 8:1 The LORD said to Moses,
04Nm 8:2 "Speak to Aaron and say to him, 'When you set up the seven lamps, they are to light the area in front of the lampstand.'"
04Nm 8:3 Aaron did so; he set up the lamps so that they faced forward on the lampstand, just as the LORD commanded Moses.
04Nm 8:4 This is how the lampstand was made£º It was made of hammered gold--from its base to its blossoms. The lampstand was made exactly like the pattern the LORD had shown Moses.
04Nm 8:5 The LORD said to Moses£º
04Nm 8:6 "Take the Levites from among the other Israelites and make them ceremonially clean.
04Nm 8:7 To purify them, do this£º Sprinkle the water of cleansing on them; then have them shave their whole bodies and wash their clothes, and so purify themselves.
04Nm 8:8 Have them take a young bull with its grain offering of fine flour mixed with oil; then you are to take a second young bull for a sin offering.
04Nm 8:9 Bring the Levites to the front of the Tent of Meeting and assemble the whole Israelite community.
04Nm 8:10 You are to bring the Levites before the LORD, and the Israelites are to lay their hands on them.
04Nm 8:11 Aaron is to present the Levites before the LORD as a wave offering from the Israelites, so that they may be ready to do the work of the LORD.
04Nm 8:12 "After the Levites lay their hands on the heads of the bulls, use the one for a sin offering to the LORD and the other for a burnt offering, to make atonement for the Levites.
04Nm 8:13 Have the Levites stand in front of Aaron and his sons and then present them as a wave offering to the LORD.
04Nm 8:14 In this way you are to set the Levites apart from the other Israelites, and the Levites will be mine.
04Nm 8:15 "After you have purified the Levites and presented them as a wave offering, they are to come to do their work at the Tent of Meeting.
04Nm 8:16 They are the Israelites who are to be given wholly to me. I have taken them as my own in place of the firstborn, the first male offspring from every Israelite woman.
04Nm 8:17 Every firstborn male in Israel, whether man or animal, is mine. When I struck down all the firstborn in Egypt, I set them apart for myself.
04Nm 8:18 And I have taken the Levites in place of all the firstborn sons in Israel.
04Nm 8:19 Of all the Israelites, I have given the Levites as gifts to Aaron and his sons to do the work at the Tent of Meeting on behalf of the Israelites and to make atonement for them so that no plague will strike the Israelites when they go near the sanctuary."
04Nm 8:20 Moses, Aaron and the whole Israelite community did with the Levites just as the LORD commanded Moses.
04Nm 8:21 The Levites purified themselves and washed their clothes. Then Aaron presented them as a wave offering before the LORD and made atonement for them to purify them.
04Nm 8:22 After that, the Levites came to do their work at the Tent of Meeting under the supervision of Aaron and his sons. They did with the Levites just as the LORD commanded Moses.
04Nm 8:23 The LORD said to Moses,
04Nm 8:24 "This applies to the Levites£º Men twenty-five years old or more shall come to take part in the work at the Tent of Meeting,
04Nm 8:25 but at the age of fifty, they must retire from their regular service and work no longer.
04Nm 8:26 They may assist their brothers in performing their duties at the Tent of Meeting, but they themselves must not do the work. This, then, is how you are to assign the responsibilities of the Levites."
04Nm 9:1 The LORD spoke to Moses in the Desert of Sinai in the first month of the second year after they came out of Egypt. He said,
04Nm 9:2 "Have the Israelites celebrate the Passover at the appointed time.
04Nm 9:3 Celebrate it at the appointed time, at twilight on the fourteenth day of this month, in accordance with all its rules and regulations."
04Nm 9:4 So Moses told the Israelites to celebrate the Passover,
04Nm 9:5 and they did so in the Desert of Sinai at twilight on the fourteenth day of the first month. The Israelites did everything just as the LORD commanded Moses.
04Nm 9:6 But some of them could not celebrate the Passover on that day because they were ceremonially unclean on account of a dead body. So they came to Moses and Aaron that same day
04Nm 9:7 and said to Moses, "We have become unclean because of a dead body, but why should we be kept from presenting the LORD'S offering with the other Israelites at the appointed time?"
04Nm 9:8 Moses answered them, "Wait until I find out what the LORD commands concerning you."
04Nm 9:9 Then the LORD said to Moses,
04Nm 9:10 "Tell the Israelites£º 'When any of you or your descendants are unclean because of a dead body or are away on a journey, they may still celebrate the LORD'S Passover.
04Nm 9:11 They are to celebrate it on the fourteenth day of the second month at twilight. They are to eat the lamb, together with unleavened bread and bitter herbs.
04Nm 9:12 They must not leave any of it till morning or break any of its bones. When they celebrate the Passover, they must follow all the regulations.
04Nm 9:13 But if a man who is ceremonially clean and not on a journey fails to celebrate the Passover, that person must be cut off from his people because he did not present the LORD'S offering at the appointed time. That man will bear the consequences of his sin.
04Nm 9:14 "'An alien living among you who wants to celebrate the LORD'S Passover must do so in accordance with its rules and regulations. You must have the same regulations for the alien and the native-born.'"
04Nm 9:15 On the day the tabernacle, the Tent of the Testimony, was set up, the cloud covered it. From evening till morning the cloud above the tabernacle looked like fire.
04Nm 9:16 That is how it continued to be; the cloud covered it, and at night it looked like fire.
04Nm 9:17 Whenever the cloud lifted from above the Tent, the Israelites set out; wherever the cloud settled, the Israelites encamped.
04Nm 9:18 At the LORD'S command the Israelites set out, and at his command they encamped. As long as the cloud stayed over the tabernacle, they remained in camp.
04Nm 9:19 When the cloud remained over the tabernacle a long time, the Israelites obeyed the LORD'S order and did not set out.
04Nm 9:20 Sometimes the cloud was over the tabernacle only a few days; at the LORD'S command they would encamp, and then at his command they would set out.
04Nm 9:21 Sometimes the cloud stayed only from evening till morning, and when it lifted in the morning, they set out. Whether by day or by night, whenever the cloud lifted, they set out.
04Nm 9:22 Whether the cloud stayed over the tabernacle for two days or a month or a year, the Israelites would remain in camp and not set out; but when it lifted, they would set out.
04Nm 9:23 At the LORD'S command they encamped, and at the LORD'S command they set out. They obeyed the LORD'S order, in accordance with his command through Moses.
04Nm 10:1 The LORD said to Moses£º
04Nm 10:2 "Make two trumpets of hammered silver, and use them for calling the community together and for having the camps set out.
04Nm 10:3 When both are sounded, the whole community is to assemble before you at the entrance to the Tent of Meeting.
04Nm 10:4 If only one is sounded, the leaders--the heads of the clans of Israel--are to assemble before you.
04Nm 10:5 When a trumpet blast is sounded, the tribes camping on the east are to set out.
04Nm 10:6 At the sounding of a second blast, the camps on the south are to set out. The blast will be the signal for setting out.
04Nm 10:7 To gather the assembly, blow the trumpets, but not with the same signal.
04Nm 10:8 "The sons of Aaron, the priests, are to blow the trumpets. This is to be a lasting ordinance for you and the generations to come.
04Nm 10:9 When you go into battle in your own land against an enemy who is oppressing you, sound a blast on the trumpets. Then you will be remembered by the LORD your God and rescued from your enemies.
04Nm 10:10 Also at your times of rejoicing--your appointed feasts and New Moon festivals--you are to sound the trumpets over your burnt offerings and fellowship offerings, and they will be a memorial for you before your God. I am the LORD your God."
04Nm 10:11 On the twentieth day of the second month of the second year, the cloud lifted from above the tabernacle of the Testimony.
04Nm 10:12 Then the Israelites set out from the Desert of Sinai and traveled from place to place until the cloud came to rest in the Desert of Paran.
04Nm 10:13 They set out, this first time, at the LORD'S command through Moses.
04Nm 10:14 The divisions of the camp of Judah went first, under their standard. Nahshon son of Amminadab was in command.
04Nm 10:15 Nethanel son of Zuar was over the division of the tribe of Issachar,
04Nm 10:16 and Eliab son of Helon was over the division of the tribe of Zebulun.
04Nm 10:17 Then the tabernacle was taken down, and the Gershonites and Merarites, who carried it, set out.
04Nm 10:18 The divisions of the camp of Reuben went next, under their standard. Elizur son of Shedeur was in command.
04Nm 10:19 Shelumiel son of Zurishaddai was over the division of the tribe of Simeon,
04Nm 10:20 and Eliasaph son of Deuel was over the division of the tribe of Gad.
04Nm 10:21 Then the Kohathites set out, carrying the holy things. The tabernacle was to be set up before they arrived.
04Nm 10:22 The divisions of the camp of Ephraim went next, under their standard. Elishama son of Ammihud was in command.
04Nm 10:23 Gamaliel son of Pedahzur was over the division of the tribe of Manasseh,
04Nm 10:24 and Abidan son of Gideoni was over the division of the tribe of Benjamin.
04Nm 10:25 Finally, as the rear guard for all the units, the divisions of the camp of Dan set out, under their standard. Ahiezer son of Ammishaddai was in command.
04Nm 10:26 Pagiel son of Ocran was over the division of the tribe of Asher,
04Nm 10:27 and Ahira son of Enan was over the division of the tribe of Naphtali.
04Nm 10:28 This was the order of march for the Israelite divisions as they set out.
04Nm 10:29 Now Moses said to Hobab son of Reuel the Midianite, Moses' father-in-law, "We are setting out for the place about which the LORD said, 'I will give it to you.' Come with us and we will treat you well, for the LORD has promised good things to Israel."
04Nm 10:30 He answered, "No, I will not go; I am going back to my own land and my own people."
04Nm 10:31 But Moses said, "Please do not leave us. You know where we should camp in the desert, and you can be our eyes.
04Nm 10:32 If you come with us, we will share with you whatever good things the LORD gives us."
04Nm 10:33 So they set out from the mountain of the LORD and traveled for three days. The ark of the covenant of the LORD went before them during those three days to find them a place to rest.
04Nm 10:34 The cloud of the LORD was over them by day when they set out from the camp.
04Nm 10:35 Whenever the ark set out, Moses said, "Rise up, O LORD! May your enemies be scattered; may your foes flee before you."
04Nm 10:36 Whenever it came to rest, he said, "Return, O LORD, to the countless thousands of Israel."
04Nm 11:1 Now the people complained about their hardships in the hearing of the LORD, and when he heard them his anger was aroused. Then fire from the LORD burned among them and consumed some of the outskirts of the camp.
04Nm 11:2 When the people cried out to Moses, he prayed to the LORD and the fire died down.
04Nm 11:3 So that place was called Taberah, because fire from the LORD had burned among them.
04Nm 11:4 The rabble with them began to crave other food, and again the Israelites started wailing and said, "If only we had meat to eat!
04Nm 11:5 We remember the fish we ate in Egypt at no cost--also the cucumbers, melons, leeks, onions and garlic.
04Nm 11:6 But now we have lost our appetite; we never see anything but this manna!"
04Nm 11:7 The manna was like coriander seed and looked like resin.
04Nm 11:8 The people went around gathering it, and then ground it in a handmill or crushed it in a mortar. They cooked it in a pot or made it into cakes. And it tasted like something made with olive oil.
04Nm 11:9 When the dew settled on the camp at night, the manna also came down.
04Nm 11:10 Moses heard the people of every family wailing, each at the entrance to his tent. The LORD became exceedingly angry, and Moses was troubled.
04Nm 11:11 He asked the LORD, "Why have you brought this trouble on your servant? What have I done to displease you that you put the burden of all these people on me?
04Nm 11:12 Did I conceive all these people? Did I give them birth? Why do you tell me to carry them in my arms, as a nurse carries an infant, to the land you promised on oath to their forefathers?
04Nm 11:13 Where can I get meat for all these people? They keep wailing to me, 'Give us meat to eat!'
04Nm 11:14 I cannot carry all these people by myself; the burden is too heavy for me.
04Nm 11:15 If this is how you are going to treat me, put me to death right now--if I have found favor in your eyes--and do not let me face my own ruin."
04Nm 11:16 The LORD said to Moses£º "Bring me seventy of Israel's elders who are known to you as leaders and officials among the people. Have them come to the Tent of Meeting, that they may stand there with you.
04Nm 11:17 I will come down and speak with you there, and I will take of the Spirit that is on you and put the Spirit on them. They will help you carry the burden of the people so that you will not have to carry it alone.
04Nm 11:18 "Tell the people£º 'Consecrate yourselves in preparation for tomorrow, when you will eat meat. The LORD heard you when you wailed, "If only we had meat to eat! We were better off in Egypt!" Now the LORD will give you meat, and you will eat it.
04Nm 11:19 You will not eat it for just one day, or two days, or five, ten or twenty days,
04Nm 11:20 but for a whole month--until it comes out of your nostrils and you loathe it--because you have rejected the LORD, who is among you, and have wailed before him, saying, "Why did we ever leave Egypt?" '"
04Nm 11:21 But Moses said, "Here I am among six hundred thousand men on foot, and you say, 'I will give them meat to eat for a whole month!'
04Nm 11:22 Would they have enough if flocks and herds were slaughtered for them? Would they have enough if all the fish in the sea were caught for them?"
04Nm 11:23 The LORD answered Moses, "Is the LORD'S arm too short? You will now see whether or not what I say will come true for you."
04Nm 11:24 So Moses went out and told the people what the LORD had said. He brought together seventy of their elders and had them stand around the Tent.
04Nm 11:25 Then the LORD came down in the cloud and spoke with him, and he took of the Spirit that was on him and put the Spirit on the seventy elders. When the Spirit rested on them, they prophesied, but they did not do so again.
04Nm 11:26 However, two men, whose names were Eldad and Medad, had remained in the camp. They were listed among the elders, but did not go out to the Tent. Yet the Spirit also rested on them, and they prophesied in the camp.
04Nm 11:27 A young man ran and told Moses, "Eldad and Medad are prophesying in the camp."
04Nm 11:28 Joshua son of Nun, who had been Moses' aide since youth, spoke up and said, "Moses, my lord, stop them!"
04Nm 11:29 But Moses replied, "Are you jealous for my sake? I wish that all the LORD'S people were prophets and that the LORD would put his Spirit on them!"
04Nm 11:30 Then Moses and the elders of Israel returned to the camp.
04Nm 11:31 Now a wind went out from the LORD and drove quail in from the sea. It brought them down all around the camp to about three feet above the ground, as far as a day's walk in any direction.
04Nm 11:32 All that day and night and all the next day the people went out and gathered quail. No one gathered less than ten homers. Then they spread them out all around the camp.
04Nm 11:33 But while the meat was still between their teeth and before it could be consumed, the anger of the LORD burned against the people, and he struck them with a severe plague.
04Nm 11:34 Therefore the place was named Kibroth Hattaavah, because there they buried the people who had craved other food.
04Nm 11:35 From Kibroth Hattaavah the people traveled to Hazeroth and stayed there.
04Nm 12:1 Miriam and Aaron began to talk against Moses because of his Cushite wife, for he had married a Cushite.
04Nm 12:2 "Has the LORD spoken only through Moses?" they asked. "Hasn't he also spoken through us?" And the LORD heard this.
04Nm 12:3 (Now Moses was a very humble man, more humble than anyone else on the face of the earth.)
04Nm 12:4 At once the LORD said to Moses, Aaron and Miriam, "Come out to the Tent of Meeting, all three of you." So the three of them came out.
04Nm 12:5 Then the LORD came down in a pillar of cloud; he stood at the entrance to the Tent and summoned Aaron and Miriam. When both of them stepped forward,
04Nm 12:6 he said, "Listen to my words£º "When a prophet of the LORD is among you, I reveal myself to him in visions, I speak to him in dreams.
04Nm 12:7 But this is not true of my servant Moses; he is faithful in all my house.
04Nm 12:8 With him I speak face to face, clearly and not in riddles; he sees the form of the LORD. Why then were you not afraid to speak against my servant Moses?"
04Nm 12:9 The anger of the LORD burned against them, and he left them.
04Nm 12:10 When the cloud lifted from above the Tent, there stood Miriam--leprous, like snow. Aaron turned toward her and saw that she had leprosy;
04Nm 12:11 and he said to Moses, "Please, my lord, do not hold against us the sin we have so foolishly committed.
04Nm 12:12 Do not let her be like a stillborn infant coming from its mother's womb with its flesh half eaten away."
04Nm 12:13 So Moses cried out to the LORD, "O God, please heal her!"
04Nm 12:14 The LORD replied to Moses, "If her father had spit in her face, would she not have been in disgrace for seven days? Confine her outside the camp for seven days; after that she can be brought back."
04Nm 12:15 So Miriam was confined outside the camp for seven days, and the people did not move on till she was brought back.
04Nm 12:16 After that, the people left Hazeroth and encamped in the Desert of Paran.
04Nm 13:1 The LORD said to Moses,
04Nm 13:2 "Send some men to explore the land of Canaan, which I am giving to the Israelites. From each ancestral tribe send one of its leaders."
04Nm 13:3 So at the LORD'S command Moses sent them out from the Desert of Paran. All of them were leaders of the Israelites.
04Nm 13:4 These are their names£º from the tribe of Reuben, Shammua son of Zaccur;
04Nm 13:5 from the tribe of Simeon, Shaphat son of Hori;
04Nm 13:6 from the tribe of Judah, Caleb son of Jephunneh;
04Nm 13:7 from the tribe of Issachar, Igal son of Joseph;
04Nm 13:8 from the tribe of Ephraim, Hoshea son of Nun;
04Nm 13:9 from the tribe of Benjamin, Palti son of Raphu;
04Nm 13:10 from the tribe of Zebulun, Gaddiel son of Sodi;
04Nm 13:11 from the tribe of Manasseh (a tribe of Joseph), Gaddi son of Susi;
04Nm 13:12 from the tribe of Dan, Ammiel son of Gemalli;
04Nm 13:13 from the tribe of Asher, Sethur son of Michael;
04Nm 13:14 from the tribe of Naphtali, Nahbi son of Vophsi;
04Nm 13:15 from the tribe of Gad, Geuel son of Maki.
04Nm 13:16 These are the names of the men Moses sent to explore the land. (Moses gave Hoshea son of Nun the name Joshua.)
04Nm 13:17 When Moses sent them to explore Canaan, he said, "Go up through the Negev and on into the hill country.
04Nm 13:18 See what the land is like and whether the people who live there are strong or weak, few or many.
04Nm 13:19 What kind of land do they live in? Is it good or bad? What kind of towns do they live in? Are they unwalled or fortified?
04Nm 13:20 How is the soil? Is it fertile or poor? Are there trees on it or not? Do your best to bring back some of the fruit of the land." (It was the season for the first ripe grapes.)
04Nm 13:21 So they went up and explored the land from the Desert of Zin as far as Rehob, toward Lebo Hamath.
04Nm 13:22 They went up through the Negev and came to Hebron, where Ahiman, Sheshai and Talmai, the descendants of Anak, lived. (Hebron had been built seven years before Zoan in Egypt.)
04Nm 13:23 When they reached the Valley of Eshcol, they cut off a branch bearing a single cluster of grapes. Two of them carried it on a pole between them, along with some pomegranates and figs.
04Nm 13:24 That place was called the Valley of Eshcol because of the cluster of grapes the Israelites cut off there.
04Nm 13:25 At the end of forty days they returned from exploring the land.
04Nm 13:26 They came back to Moses and Aaron and the whole Israelite community at Kadesh in the Desert of Paran. There they reported to them and to the whole assembly and showed them the fruit of the land.
04Nm 13:27 They gave Moses this account£º "We went into the land to which you sent us, and it does flow with milk and honey! Here is its fruit.
04Nm 13:28 But the people who live there are powerful, and the cities are fortified and very large. We even saw descendants of Anak there.
04Nm 13:29 The Amalekites live in the Negev; the Hittites, Jebusites and Amorites live in the hill country; and the Canaanites live near the sea and along the Jordan."
04Nm 13:30 Then Caleb silenced the people before Moses and said, "We should go up and take possession of the land, for we can certainly do it."
04Nm 13:31 But the men who had gone up with him said, "We can't attack those people; they are stronger than we are."
04Nm 13:32 And they spread among the Israelites a bad report about the land they had explored. They said, "The land we explored devours those living in it. All the people we saw there are of great size.
04Nm 13:33 We saw the Nephilim there (the descendants of Anak come from the Nephilim). We seemed like grasshoppers in our own eyes, and we looked the same to them."
04Nm 14:1 That night all the people of the community raised their voices and wept aloud.
04Nm 14:2 All the Israelites grumbled against Moses and Aaron, and the whole assembly said to them, "If only we had died in Egypt! Or in this desert!
04Nm 14:3 Why is the LORD bringing us to this land only to let us fall by the sword? Our wives and children will be taken as plunder. Wouldn't it be better for us to go back to Egypt?"
04Nm 14:4 And they said to each other, "We should choose a leader and go back to Egypt."
04Nm 14:5 Then Moses and Aaron fell facedown in front of the whole Israelite assembly gathered there.
04Nm 14:6 Joshua son of Nun and Caleb son of Jephunneh, who were among those who had explored the land, tore their clothes
04Nm 14:7 and said to the entire Israelite assembly, "The land we passed through and explored is exceedingly good.
04Nm 14:8 If the LORD is pleased with us, he will lead us into that land, a land flowing with milk and honey, and will give it to us.
04Nm 14:9 Only do not rebel against the LORD. And do not be afraid of the people of the land, because we will swallow them up. Their protection is gone, but the LORD is with us. Do not be afraid of them."
04Nm 14:10 But the whole assembly talked about stoning them. Then the glory of the LORD appeared at the Tent of Meeting to all the Israelites.
04Nm 14:11 The LORD said to Moses, "How long will these people treat me with contempt? How long will they refuse to believe in me, in spite of all the miraculous signs I have performed among them?
04Nm 14:12 I will strike them down with a plague and destroy them, but I will make you into a nation greater and stronger than they."
04Nm 14:13 Moses said to the LORD, "Then the Egyptians will hear about it! By your power you brought these people up from among them.
04Nm 14:14 And they will tell the inhabitants of this land about it. They have already heard that you, O LORD, are with these people and that you, O LORD, have been seen face to face, that your cloud stays over them, and that you go before them in a pillar of cloud by day and a pillar of fire by night.
04Nm 14:15 If you put these people to death all at one time, the nations who have heard this report about you will say,
04Nm 14:16 'The LORD was not able to bring these people into the land he promised them on oath; so he slaughtered them in the desert.'
04Nm 14:17 "Now may the Lord's strength be displayed, just as you have declared£º
04Nm 14:18 'The LORD is slow to anger, abounding in love and forgiving sin and rebellion. Yet he does not leave the guilty unpunished; he punishes the children for the sin of the fathers to the third and fourth generation.'
04Nm 14:19 In accordance with your great love, forgive the sin of these people, just as you have pardoned them from the time they left Egypt until now."
04Nm 14:20 The LORD replied, "I have forgiven them, as you asked.
04Nm 14:21 Nevertheless, as surely as I live and as surely as the glory of the LORD fills the whole earth,
04Nm 14:22 not one of the men who saw my glory and the miraculous signs I performed in Egypt and in the desert but who disobeyed me and tested me ten times--
04Nm 14:23 not one of them will ever see the land I promised on oath to their forefathers. No one who has treated me with contempt will ever see it.
04Nm 14:24 But because my servant Caleb has a different spirit and follows me wholeheartedly, I will bring him into the land he went to, and his descendants will inherit it.
04Nm 14:25 Since the Amalekites and Canaanites are living in the valleys, turn back tomorrow and set out toward the desert along the route to the Red Sea."
04Nm 14:26 The LORD said to Moses and Aaron£º
04Nm 14:27 "How long will this wicked community grumble against me? I have heard the complaints of these grumbling Israelites.
04Nm 14:28 So tell them, 'As surely as I live, declares the LORD, I will do to you the very things I heard you say£º
04Nm 14:29 In this desert your bodies will fall--every one of you twenty years old or more who was counted in the census and who has grumbled against me.
04Nm 14:30 Not one of you will enter the land I swore with uplifted hand to make your home, except Caleb son of Jephunneh and Joshua son of Nun.
04Nm 14:31 As for your children that you said would be taken as plunder, I will bring them in to enjoy the land you have rejected.
04Nm 14:32 But you--your bodies will fall in this desert.
04Nm 14:33 Your children will be shepherds here for forty years, suffering for your unfaithfulness, until the last of your bodies lies in the desert.
04Nm 14:34 For forty years--one year for each of the forty days you explored the land--you will suffer for your sins and know what it is like to have me against you.'
04Nm 14:35 I, the LORD, have spoken, and I will surely do these things to this whole wicked community, which has banded together against me. They will meet their end in this desert; here they will die."
04Nm 14:36 So the men Moses had sent to explore the land, who returned and made the whole community grumble against him by spreading a bad report about it--
04Nm 14:37 these men responsible for spreading the bad report about the land were struck down and died of a plague before the LORD.
04Nm 14:38 Of the men who went to explore the land, only Joshua son of Nun and Caleb son of Jephunneh survived.
04Nm 14:39 When Moses reported this to all the Israelites, they mourned bitterly.
04Nm 14:40 Early the next morning they went up toward the high hill country. "We have sinned," they said. "We will go up to the place the LORD promised."
04Nm 14:41 But Moses said, "Why are you disobeying the LORD'S command? This will not succeed!
04Nm 14:42 Do not go up, because the LORD is not with you. You will be defeated by your enemies,
04Nm 14:43 for the Amalekites and Canaanites will face you there. Because you have turned away from the LORD, he will not be with you and you will fall by the sword."
04Nm 14:44 Nevertheless, in their presumption they went up toward the high hill country, though neither Moses nor the ark of the LORD'S covenant moved from the camp.
04Nm 14:45 Then the Amalekites and Canaanites who lived in that hill country came down and attacked them and beat them down all the way to Hormah.
04Nm 15:1 The LORD said to Moses,
04Nm 15:2 "Speak to the Israelites and say to them£º 'After you enter the land I am giving you as a home
04Nm 15:3 and you present to the LORD offerings made by fire, from the herd or the flock, as an aroma pleasing to the LORD--whether burnt offerings or sacrifices, for special vows or freewill offerings or festival offerings--
04Nm 15:4 then the one who brings his offering shall present to the LORD a grain offering of a tenth of an ephah of fine flour mixed with a quarter of a hin of oil.
04Nm 15:5 With each lamb for the burnt offering or the sacrifice, prepare a quarter of a hin of wine as a drink offering.
04Nm 15:6 "'With a ram prepare a grain offering of two-tenths of an ephah of fine flour mixed with a third of a hin of oil,
04Nm 15:7 and a third of a hin of wine as a drink offering. Offer it as an aroma pleasing to the LORD.
04Nm 15:8 "'When you prepare a young bull as a burnt offering or sacrifice, for a special vow or a fellowship offering to the LORD,
04Nm 15:9 bring with the bull a grain offering of three-tenths of an ephah of fine flour mixed with half a hin of oil.
04Nm 15:10 Also bring half a hin of wine as a drink offering. It will be an offering made by fire, an aroma pleasing to the LORD.
04Nm 15:11 Each bull or ram, each lamb or young goat, is to be prepared in this manner.
04Nm 15:12 Do this for each one, for as many as you prepare.
04Nm 15:13 "'Everyone who is native-born must do these things in this way when he brings an offering made by fire as an aroma pleasing to the LORD.
04Nm 15:14 For the generations to come, whenever an alien or anyone else living among you presents an offering made by fire as an aroma pleasing to the LORD, he must do exactly as you do.
04Nm 15:15 The community is to have the same rules for you and for the alien living among you; this is a lasting ordinance for the generations to come. You and the alien shall be the same before the LORD£º
04Nm 15:16 The same laws and regulations will apply both to you and to the alien living among you.'"
04Nm 15:17 The LORD said to Moses,
04Nm 15:18 "Speak to the Israelites and say to them£º 'When you enter the land to which I am taking you
04Nm 15:19 and you eat the food of the land, present a portion as an offering to the LORD.
04Nm 15:20 Present a cake from the first of your ground meal and present it as an offering from the threshing floor.
04Nm 15:21 Throughout the generations to come you are to give this offering to the LORD from the first of your ground meal.
04Nm 15:22 "'Now if you unintentionally fail to keep any of these commands the LORD gave Moses--
04Nm 15:23 any of the LORD'S commands to you through him, from the day the LORD gave them and continuing through the generations to come--
04Nm 15:24 and if this is done unintentionally without the community being aware of it, then the whole community is to offer a young bull for a burnt offering as an aroma pleasing to the LORD, along with its prescribed grain offering and drink offering, and a male goat for a sin offering.
04Nm 15:25 The priest is to make atonement for the whole Israelite community, and they will be forgiven, for it was not intentional and they have brought to the LORD for their wrong an offering made by fire and a sin offering.
04Nm 15:26 The whole Israelite community and the aliens living among them will be forgiven, because all the people were involved in the unintentional wrong.
04Nm 15:27 "'But if just one person sins unintentionally, he must bring a year-old female goat for a sin offering.
04Nm 15:28 The priest is to make atonement before the LORD for the one who erred by sinning unintentionally, and when atonement has been made for him, he will be forgiven.
04Nm 15:29 One and the same law applies to everyone who sins unintentionally, whether he is a native-born Israelite or an alien.
04Nm 15:30 "'But anyone who sins defiantly, whether native-born or alien, blasphemes the LORD, and that person must be cut off from his people.
04Nm 15:31 Because he has despised the LORD'S word and broken his commands, that person must surely be cut off; his guilt remains on him.'"
04Nm 15:32 While the Israelites were in the desert, a man was found gathering wood on the Sabbath day.
04Nm 15:33 Those who found him gathering wood brought him to Moses and Aaron and the whole assembly,
04Nm 15:34 and they kept him in custody, because it was not clear what should be done to him.
04Nm 15:35 Then the LORD said to Moses, "The man must die. The whole assembly must stone him outside the camp."
04Nm 15:36 So the assembly took him outside the camp and stoned him to death, as the LORD commanded Moses.
04Nm 15:37 The LORD said to Moses,
04Nm 15:38 "Speak to the Israelites and say to them£º 'Throughout the generations to come you are to make tassels on the corners of your garments, with a blue cord on each tassel.
04Nm 15:39 You will have these tassels to look at and so you will remember all the commands of the LORD, that you may obey them and not prostitute yourselves by going after the lusts of your own hearts and eyes.
04Nm 15:40 Then you will remember to obey all my commands and will be consecrated to your God.
04Nm 15:41 I am the LORD your God, who brought you out of Egypt to be your God. I am the LORD your God.'"
04Nm 16:1 Korah son of Izhar, the son of Kohath, the son of Levi, and certain Reubenites--Dathan and Abiram, sons of Eliab, and On son of Peleth--became insolent
04Nm 16:2 and rose up against Moses. With them were 250 Israelite men, well-known community leaders who had been appointed members of the council.
04Nm 16:3 They came as a group to oppose Moses and Aaron and said to them, "You have gone too far! The whole community is holy, every one of them, and the LORD is with them. Why then do you set yourselves above the LORD'S assembly?"
04Nm 16:4 When Moses heard this, he fell facedown.
04Nm 16:5 Then he said to Korah and all his followers£º "In the morning the LORD will show who belongs to him and who is holy, and he will have that person come near him. The man he chooses he will cause to come near him.
04Nm 16:6 You, Korah, and all your followers are to do this£º Take censers
04Nm 16:7 and tomorrow put fire and incense in them before the LORD. The man the LORD chooses will be the one who is holy. You Levites have gone too far!"
04Nm 16:8 Moses also said to Korah, "Now listen, you Levites!
04Nm 16:9 Isn't it enough for you that the God of Israel has separated you from the rest of the Israelite community and brought you near himself to do the work at the LORD'S tabernacle and to stand before the community and minister to them?
04Nm 16:10 He has brought you and all your fellow Levites near himself, but now you are trying to get the priesthood too.
04Nm 16:11 It is against the LORD that you and all your followers have banded together. Who is Aaron that you should grumble against him?"
04Nm 16:12 Then Moses summoned Dathan and Abiram, the sons of Eliab. But they said, "We will not come!
04Nm 16:13 Isn't it enough that you have brought us up out of a land flowing with milk and honey to kill us in the desert? And now you also want to lord it over us?
04Nm 16:14 Moreover, you haven't brought us into a land flowing with milk and honey or given us an inheritance of fields and vineyards. Will you gouge out the eyes of these men? No, we will not come!"
04Nm 16:15 Then Moses became very angry and said to the LORD, "Do not accept their offering. I have not taken so much as a donkey from them, nor have I wronged any of them."
04Nm 16:16 Moses said to Korah, "You and all your followers are to appear before the LORD tomorrow--you and they and Aaron.
04Nm 16:17 Each man is to take his censer and put incense in it--250 censers in all--and present it before the LORD. You and Aaron are to present your censers also."
04Nm 16:18 So each man took his censer, put fire and incense in it, and stood with Moses and Aaron at the entrance to the Tent of Meeting.
04Nm 16:19 When Korah had gathered all his followers in opposition to them at the entrance to the Tent of Meeting, the glory of the LORD appeared to the entire assembly.
04Nm 16:20 The LORD said to Moses and Aaron,
04Nm 16:21 "Separate yourselves from this assembly so I can put an end to them at once."
04Nm 16:22 But Moses and Aaron fell facedown and cried out, "O God, God of the spirits of all mankind, will you be angry with the entire assembly when only one man sins?"
04Nm 16:23 Then the LORD said to Moses,
04Nm 16:24 "Say to the assembly, 'Move away from the tents of Korah, Dathan and Abiram.'"
04Nm 16:25 Moses got up and went to Dathan and Abiram, and the elders of Israel followed him.
04Nm 16:26 He warned the assembly, "Move back from the tents of these wicked men! Do not touch anything belonging to them, or you will be swept away because of all their sins."
04Nm 16:27 So they moved away from the tents of Korah, Dathan and Abiram. Dathan and Abiram had come out and were standing with their wives, children and little ones at the entrances to their tents.
04Nm 16:28 Then Moses said, "This is how you will know that the LORD has sent me to do all these things and that it was not my idea£º
04Nm 16:29 If these men die a natural death and experience only what usually happens to men, then the LORD has not sent me.
04Nm 16:30 But if the LORD brings about something totally new, and the earth opens its mouth and swallows them, with everything that belongs to them, and they go down alive into the grave, then you will know that these men have treated the LORD with contempt."
04Nm 16:31 As soon as he finished saying all this, the ground under them split apart
04Nm 16:32 and the earth opened its mouth and swallowed them, with their households and all Korah's men and all their possessions.
04Nm 16:33 They went down alive into the grave, with everything they owned; the earth closed over them, and they perished and were gone from the community.
04Nm 16:34 At their cries, all the Israelites around them fled, shouting, "The earth is going to swallow us too!"
04Nm 16:35 And fire came out from the LORD and consumed the 250 men who were offering the incense.
04Nm 16:36 The LORD said to Moses,
04Nm 16:37 "Tell Eleazar son of Aaron, the priest, to take the censers out of the smoldering remains and scatter the coals some distance away, for the censers are holy--
04Nm 16:38 the censers of the men who sinned at the cost of their lives. Hammer the censers into sheets to overlay the altar, for they were presented before the LORD and have become holy. Let them be a sign to the Israelites."
04Nm 16:39 So Eleazar the priest collected the bronze censers brought by those who had been burned up, and he had them hammered out to overlay the altar,
04Nm 16:40 as the LORD directed him through Moses. This was to remind the Israelites that no one except a descendant of Aaron should come to burn incense before the LORD, or he would become like Korah and his followers.
04Nm 16:41 The next day the whole Israelite community grumbled against Moses and Aaron. "You have killed the LORD'S people," they said.
04Nm 16:42 But when the assembly gathered in opposition to Moses and Aaron and turned toward the Tent of Meeting, suddenly the cloud covered it and the glory of the LORD appeared.
04Nm 16:43 Then Moses and Aaron went to the front of the Tent of Meeting,
04Nm 16:44 and the LORD said to Moses,
04Nm 16:45 "Get away from this assembly so I can put an end to them at once." And they fell facedown.
04Nm 16:46 Then Moses said to Aaron, "Take your censer and put incense in it, along with fire from the altar, and hurry to the assembly to make atonement for them. Wrath has come out from the LORD; the plague has started."
04Nm 16:47 So Aaron did as Moses said, and ran into the midst of the assembly. The plague had already started among the people, but Aaron offered the incense and made atonement for them.
04Nm 16:48 He stood between the living and the dead, and the plague stopped.
04Nm 16:49 But 14,700 people died from the plague, in addition to those who had died because of Korah.
04Nm 16:50 Then Aaron returned to Moses at the entrance to the Tent of Meeting, for the plague had stopped.
04Nm 17:1 The LORD said to Moses,
04Nm 17:2 "Speak to the Israelites and get twelve staffs from them, one from the leader of each of their ancestral tribes. Write the name of each man on his staff.
04Nm 17:3 On the staff of Levi write Aaron's name, for there must be one staff for the head of each ancestral tribe.
04Nm 17:4 Place them in the Tent of Meeting in front of the Testimony, where I meet with you.
04Nm 17:5 The staff belonging to the man I choose will sprout, and I will rid myself of this constant grumbling against you by the Israelites."
04Nm 17:6 So Moses spoke to the Israelites, and their leaders gave him twelve staffs, one for the leader of each of their ancestral tribes, and Aaron's staff was among them.
04Nm 17:7 Moses placed the staffs before the LORD in the Tent of the Testimony.
04Nm 17:8 The next day Moses entered the Tent of the Testimony and saw that Aaron's staff, which represented the house of Levi, had not only sprouted but had budded, blossomed and produced almonds.
04Nm 17:9 Then Moses brought out all the staffs from the LORD'S presence to all the Israelites. They looked at them, and each man took his own staff.
04Nm 17:10 The LORD said to Moses, "Put back Aaron's staff in front of the Testimony, to be kept as a sign to the rebellious. This will put an end to their grumbling against me, so that they will not die."
04Nm 17:11 Moses did just as the LORD commanded him.
04Nm 17:12 The Israelites said to Moses, "We will die! We are lost, we are all lost!
04Nm 17:13 Anyone who even comes near the tabernacle of the LORD will die. Are we all going to die?"
04Nm 18:1 The LORD said to Aaron, "You, your sons and your father's family are to bear the responsibility for offenses against the sanctuary, and you and your sons alone are to bear the responsibility for offenses against the priesthood.
04Nm 18:2 Bring your fellow Levites from your ancestral tribe to join you and assist you when you and your sons minister before the Tent of the Testimony.
04Nm 18:3 They are to be responsible to you and are to perform all the duties of the Tent, but they must not go near the furnishings of the sanctuary or the altar, or both they and you will die.
04Nm 18:4 They are to join you and be responsible for the care of the Tent of Meeting--all the work at the Tent--and no one else may come near where you are.
04Nm 18:5 "You are to be responsible for the care of the sanctuary and the altar, so that wrath will not fall on the Israelites again.
04Nm 18:6 I myself have selected your fellow Levites from among the Israelites as a gift to you, dedicated to the LORD to do the work at the Tent of Meeting.
04Nm 18:7 But only you and your sons may serve as priests in connection with everything at the altar and inside the curtain. I am giving you the service of the priesthood as a gift. Anyone else who comes near the sanctuary must be put to death."
04Nm 18:8 Then the LORD said to Aaron, "I myself have put you in charge of the offerings presented to me; all the holy offerings the Israelites give me I give to you and your sons as your portion and regular share.
04Nm 18:9 You are to have the part of the most holy offerings that is kept from the fire. From all the gifts they bring me as most holy offerings, whether grain or sin or guilt offerings, that part belongs to you and your sons.
04Nm 18:10 Eat it as something most holy; every male shall eat it. You must regard it as holy.
04Nm 18:11 "This also is yours£º whatever is set aside from the gifts of all the wave offerings of the Israelites. I give this to you and your sons and daughters as your regular share. Everyone in your household who is ceremonially clean may eat it.
04Nm 18:12 "I give you all the finest olive oil and all the finest new wine and grain they give the LORD as the firstfruits of their harvest.
04Nm 18:13 All the land's firstfruits that they bring to the LORD will be yours. Everyone in your household who is ceremonially clean may eat it.
04Nm 18:14 "Everything in Israel that is devoted to the LORD is yours.
04Nm 18:15 The first offspring of every womb, both man and animal, that is offered to the LORD is yours. But you must redeem every firstborn son and every firstborn male of unclean animals.
04Nm 18:16 When they are a month old, you must redeem them at the redemption price set at five shekels of silver, according to the sanctuary shekel, which weighs twenty gerahs.
04Nm 18:17 "But you must not redeem the firstborn of an ox, a sheep or a goat; they are holy. Sprinkle their blood on the altar and burn their fat as an offering made by fire, an aroma pleasing to the LORD.
04Nm 18:18 Their meat is to be yours, just as the breast of the wave offering and the right thigh are yours.
04Nm 18:19 Whatever is set aside from the holy offerings the Israelites present to the LORD I give to you and your sons and daughters as your regular share. It is an everlasting covenant of salt before the LORD for both you and your offspring."
04Nm 18:20 The LORD said to Aaron, "You will have no inheritance in their land, nor will you have any share among them; I am your share and your inheritance among the Israelites.
04Nm 18:21 "I give to the Levites all the tithes in Israel as their inheritance in return for the work they do while serving at the Tent of Meeting.
04Nm 18:22 From now on the Israelites must not go near the Tent of Meeting, or they will bear the consequences of their sin and will die.
04Nm 18:23 It is the Levites who are to do the work at the Tent of Meeting and bear the responsibility for offenses against it. This is a lasting ordinance for the generations to come. They will receive no inheritance among the Israelites.
04Nm 18:24 Instead, I give to the Levites as their inheritance the tithes that the Israelites present as an offering to the LORD. That is why I said concerning them£º 'They will have no inheritance among the Israelites.'"
04Nm 18:25 The LORD said to Moses,
04Nm 18:26 "Speak to the Levites and say to them£º 'When you receive from the Israelites the tithe I give you as your inheritance, you must present a tenth of that tithe as the LORD'S offering.
04Nm 18:27 Your offering will be reckoned to you as grain from the threshing floor or juice from the winepress.
04Nm 18:28 In this way you also will present an offering to the LORD from all the tithes you receive from the Israelites. From these tithes you must give the LORD'S portion to Aaron the priest.
04Nm 18:29 You must present as the LORD'S portion the best and holiest part of everything given to you.'
04Nm 18:30 "Say to the Levites£º 'When you present the best part, it will be reckoned to you as the product of the threshing floor or the winepress.
04Nm 18:31 You and your households may eat the rest of it anywhere, for it is your wages for your work at the Tent of Meeting.
04Nm 18:32 By presenting the best part of it you will not be guilty in this matter; then you will not defile the holy offerings of the Israelites, and you will not die.'"
04Nm 19:1 The LORD said to Moses and Aaron£º
04Nm 19:2 "This is a requirement of the law that the LORD has commanded£º Tell the Israelites to bring you a red heifer without defect or blemish and that has never been under a yoke.
04Nm 19:3 Give it to Eleazar the priest; it is to be taken outside the camp and slaughtered in his presence.
04Nm 19:4 Then Eleazar the priest is to take some of its blood on his finger and sprinkle it seven times toward the front of the Tent of Meeting.
04Nm 19:5 While he watches, the heifer is to be burned--its hide, flesh, blood and offal.
04Nm 19:6 The priest is to take some cedar wood, hyssop and scarlet wool and throw them onto the burning heifer.
04Nm 19:7 After that, the priest must wash his clothes and bathe himself with water. He may then come into the camp, but he will be ceremonially unclean till evening.
04Nm 19:8 The man who burns it must also wash his clothes and bathe with water, and he too will be unclean till evening.
04Nm 19:9 "A man who is clean shall gather up the ashes of the heifer and put them in a ceremonially clean place outside the camp. They shall be kept by the Israelite community for use in the water of cleansing; it is for purification from sin.
04Nm 19:10 The man who gathers up the ashes of the heifer must also wash his clothes, and he too will be unclean till evening. This will be a lasting ordinance both for the Israelites and for the aliens living among them.
04Nm 19:11 "Whoever touches the dead body of anyone will be unclean for seven days.
04Nm 19:12 He must purify himself with the water on the third day and on the seventh day; then he will be clean. But if he does not purify himself on the third and seventh days, he will not be clean.
04Nm 19:13 Whoever touches the dead body of anyone and fails to purify himself defiles the LORD'S tabernacle. That person must be cut off from Israel. Because the water of cleansing has not been sprinkled on him, he is unclean; his uncleanness remains on him.
04Nm 19:14 "This is the law that applies when a person dies in a tent£º Anyone who enters the tent and anyone who is in it will be unclean for seven days,
04Nm 19:15 and every open container without a lid fastened on it will be unclean.
04Nm 19:16 "Anyone out in the open who touches someone who has been killed with a sword or someone who has died a natural death, or anyone who touches a human bone or a grave, will be unclean for seven days.
04Nm 19:17 "For the unclean person, put some ashes from the burned purification offering into a jar and pour fresh water over them.
04Nm 19:18 Then a man who is ceremonially clean is to take some hyssop, dip it in the water and sprinkle the tent and all the furnishings and the people who were there. He must also sprinkle anyone who has touched a human bone or a grave or someone who has been killed or someone who has died a natural death.
04Nm 19:19 The man who is clean is to sprinkle the unclean person on the third and seventh days, and on the seventh day he is to purify him. The person being cleansed must wash his clothes and bathe with water, and that evening he will be clean.
04Nm 19:20 But if a person who is unclean does not purify himself, he must be cut off from the community, because he has defiled the sanctuary of the LORD. The water of cleansing has not been sprinkled on him, and he is unclean.
04Nm 19:21 This is a lasting ordinance for them. "The man who sprinkles the water of cleansing must also wash his clothes, and anyone who touches the water of cleansing will be unclean till evening.
04Nm 19:22 Anything that an unclean person touches becomes unclean, and anyone who touches it becomes unclean till evening."
04Nm 20:1 In the first month the whole Israelite community arrived at the Desert of Zin, and they stayed at Kadesh. There Miriam died and was buried.
04Nm 20:2 Now there was no water for the community, and the people gathered in opposition to Moses and Aaron.
04Nm 20:3 They quarreled with Moses and said, "If only we had died when our brothers fell dead before the LORD!
04Nm 20:4 Why did you bring the LORD'S community into this desert, that we and our livestock should die here?
04Nm 20:5 Why did you bring us up out of Egypt to this terrible place? It has no grain or figs, grapevines or pomegranates. And there is no water to drink!"
04Nm 20:6 Moses and Aaron went from the assembly to the entrance to the Tent of Meeting and fell facedown, and the glory of the LORD appeared to them.
04Nm 20:7 The LORD said to Moses,
04Nm 20:8 "Take the staff, and you and your brother Aaron gather the assembly together. Speak to that rock before their eyes and it will pour out its water. You will bring water out of the rock for the community so they and their livestock can drink."
04Nm 20:9 So Moses took the staff from the LORD'S presence, just as he commanded him.
04Nm 20:10 He and Aaron gathered the assembly together in front of the rock and Moses said to them, "Listen, you rebels, must we bring you water out of this rock?"
04Nm 20:11 Then Moses raised his arm and struck the rock twice with his staff. Water gushed out, and the community and their livestock drank.
04Nm 20:12 But the LORD said to Moses and Aaron, "Because you did not trust in me enough to honor me as holy in the sight of the Israelites, you will not bring this community into the land I give them."
04Nm 20:13 These were the waters of Meribah, where the Israelites quarreled with the LORD and where he showed himself holy among them.
04Nm 20:14 Moses sent messengers from Kadesh to the king of Edom, saying£º "This is what your brother Israel says£º You know about all the hardships that have come upon us.
04Nm 20:15 Our forefathers went down into Egypt, and we lived there many years. The Egyptians mistreated us and our fathers,
04Nm 20:16 but when we cried out to the LORD, he heard our cry and sent an angel and brought us out of Egypt. "Now we are here at Kadesh, a town on the edge of your territory.
04Nm 20:17 Please let us pass through your country. We will not go through any field or vineyard, or drink water from any well. We will travel along the king's highway and not turn to the right or to the left until we have passed through your territory."
04Nm 20:18 But Edom answered£º "You may not pass through here; if you try, we will march out and attack you with the sword."
04Nm 20:19 The Israelites replied£º "We will go along the main road, and if we or our livestock drink any of your water, we will pay for it. We only want to pass through on foot--nothing else."
04Nm 20:20 Again they answered£º "You may not pass through." Then Edom came out against them with a large and powerful army.
04Nm 20:21 Since Edom refused to let them go through their territory, Israel turned away from them.
04Nm 20:22 The whole Israelite community set out from Kadesh and came to Mount Hor.
04Nm 20:23 At Mount Hor, near the border of Edom, the LORD said to Moses and Aaron,
04Nm 20:24 "Aaron will be gathered to his people. He will not enter the land I give the Israelites, because both of you rebelled against my command at the waters of Meribah.
04Nm 20:25 Get Aaron and his son Eleazar and take them up Mount Hor.
04Nm 20:26 Remove Aaron's garments and put them on his son Eleazar, for Aaron will be gathered to his people; he will die there."
04Nm 20:27 Moses did as the LORD commanded£º They went up Mount Hor in the sight of the whole community.
04Nm 20:28 Moses removed Aaron's garments and put them on his son Eleazar. And Aaron died there on top of the mountain. Then Moses and Eleazar came down from the mountain,
04Nm 20:29 and when the whole community learned that Aaron had died, the entire house of Israel mourned for him thirty days.
04Nm 21:1 When the Canaanite king of Arad, who lived in the Negev, heard that Israel was coming along the road to Atharim, he attacked the Israelites and captured some of them.
04Nm 21:2 Then Israel made this vow to the LORD£º "If you will deliver these people into our hands, we will totally destroy their cities."
04Nm 21:3 The LORD listened to Israel's plea and gave the Canaanites over to them. They completely destroyed them and their towns; so the place was named Hormah.
04Nm 21:4 They traveled from Mount Hor along the route to the Red Sea, to go around Edom. But the people grew impatient on the way;
04Nm 21:5 they spoke against God and against Moses, and said, "Why have you brought us up out of Egypt to die in the desert? There is no bread! There is no water! And we detest this miserable food!"
04Nm 21:6 Then the LORD sent venomous snakes among them; they bit the people and many Israelites died.
04Nm 21:7 The people came to Moses and said, "We sinned when we spoke against the LORD and against you. Pray that the LORD will take the snakes away from us." So Moses prayed for the people.
04Nm 21:8 The LORD said to Moses, "Make a snake and put it up on a pole; anyone who is bitten can look at it and live."
04Nm 21:9 So Moses made a bronze snake and put it up on a pole. Then when anyone was bitten by a snake and looked at the bronze snake, he lived.
04Nm 21:10 The Israelites moved on and camped at Oboth.
04Nm 21:11 Then they set out from Oboth and camped in Iye Abarim, in the desert that faces Moab toward the sunrise.
04Nm 21:12 From there they moved on and camped in the Zered Valley.
04Nm 21:13 They set out from there and camped alongside the Arnon, which is in the desert extending into Amorite territory. The Arnon is the border of Moab, between Moab and the Amorites.
04Nm 21:14 That is why the Book of the Wars of the LORD says£º ". . . Waheb in Suphah and the ravines, the Arnon
04Nm 21:15 and the slopes of the ravines that lead to the site of Ar and lie along the border of Moab."
04Nm 21:16 From there they continued on to Beer, the well where the LORD said to Moses, "Gather the people together and I will give them water."
04Nm 21:17 Then Israel sang this song£º "Spring up, O well! Sing about it,
04Nm 21:18 about the well that the princes dug, that the nobles of the people sank--the nobles with scepters and staffs." Then they went from the desert to Mattanah,
04Nm 21:19 from Mattanah to Nahaliel, from Nahaliel to Bamoth,
04Nm 21:20 and from Bamoth to the valley in Moab where the top of Pisgah overlooks the wasteland.
04Nm 21:21 Israel sent messengers to say to Sihon king of the Amorites£º
04Nm 21:22 "Let us pass through your country. We will not turn aside into any field or vineyard, or drink water from any well. We will travel along the king's highway until we have passed through your territory."
04Nm 21:23 But Sihon would not let Israel pass through his territory. He mustered his entire army and marched out into the desert against Israel. When he reached Jahaz, he fought with Israel.
04Nm 21:24 Israel, however, put him to the sword and took over his land from the Arnon to the Jabbok, but only as far as the Ammonites, because their border was fortified.
04Nm 21:25 Israel captured all the cities of the Amorites and occupied them, including Heshbon and all its surrounding settlements.
04Nm 21:26 Heshbon was the city of Sihon king of the Amorites, who had fought against the former king of Moab and had taken from him all his land as far as the Arnon.
04Nm 21:27 That is why the poets say£º "Come to Heshbon and let it be rebuilt; let Sihon's city be restored.
04Nm 21:28 "Fire went out from Heshbon, a blaze from the city of Sihon. It consumed Ar of Moab, the citizens of Arnon's heights.
04Nm 21:29 Woe to you, O Moab! You are destroyed, O people of Chemosh! He has given up his sons as fugitives and his daughters as captives to Sihon king of the Amorites.
04Nm 21:30 "But we have overthrown them; Heshbon is destroyed all the way to Dibon. We have demolished them as far as Nophah, which extends to Medeba."
04Nm 21:31 So Israel settled in the land of the Amorites.
04Nm 21:32 After Moses had sent spies to Jazer, the Israelites captured its surrounding settlements and drove out the Amorites who were there.
04Nm 21:33 Then they turned and went up along the road toward Bashan, and Og king of Bashan and his whole army marched out to meet them in battle at Edrei.
04Nm 21:34 The LORD said to Moses, "Do not be afraid of him, for I have handed him over to you, with his whole army and his land. Do to him what you did to Sihon king of the Amorites, who reigned in Heshbon."
04Nm 21:35 So they struck him down, together with his sons and his whole army, leaving them no survivors. And they took possession of his land.
04Nm 22:1 Then the Israelites traveled to the plains of Moab and camped along the Jordan across from Jericho.
04Nm 22:2 Now Balak son of Zippor saw all that Israel had done to the Amorites,
04Nm 22:3 and Moab was terrified because there were so many people. Indeed, Moab was filled with dread because of the Israelites.
04Nm 22:4 The Moabites said to the elders of Midian, "This horde is going to lick up everything around us, as an ox licks up the grass of the field." So Balak son of Zippor, who was king of Moab at that time,
04Nm 22:5 sent messengers to summon Balaam son of Beor, who was at Pethor, near the River, in his native land. Balak said£º "A people has come out of Egypt; they cover the face of the land and have settled next to me.
04Nm 22:6 Now come and put a curse on these people, because they are too powerful for me. Perhaps then I will be able to defeat them and drive them out of the country. For I know that those you bless are blessed, and those you curse are cursed."
04Nm 22:7 The elders of Moab and Midian left, taking with them the fee for divination. When they came to Balaam, they told him what Balak had said.
04Nm 22:8 "Spend the night here," Balaam said to them, "and I will bring you back the answer the LORD gives me." So the Moabite princes stayed with him.
04Nm 22:9 God came to Balaam and asked, "Who are these men with you?"
04Nm 22:10 Balaam said to God, "Balak son of Zippor, king of Moab, sent me this message£º
