04Nm 30:1 Moses said to the heads of the tribes of Israel£º "This is what the LORD commands£º
04Nm 30:2 When a man makes a vow to the LORD or takes an oath to obligate himself by a pledge, he must not break his word but must do everything he said.
04Nm 30:3 "When a young woman still living in her father's house makes a vow to the LORD or obligates herself by a pledge
04Nm 30:4 and her father hears about her vow or pledge but says nothing to her, then all her vows and every pledge by which she obligated herself will stand.
04Nm 30:5 But if her father forbids her when he hears about it, none of her vows or the pledges by which she obligated herself will stand; the LORD will release her because her father has forbidden her.
04Nm 30:6 "If she marries after she makes a vow or after her lips utter a rash promise by which she obligates herself
04Nm 30:7 and her husband hears about it but says nothing to her, then her vows or the pledges by which she obligated herself will stand.
04Nm 30:8 But if her husband forbids her when he hears about it, he nullifies the vow that obligates her or the rash promise by which she obligates herself, and the LORD will release her.
04Nm 30:9 "Any vow or obligation taken by a widow or divorced woman will be binding on her.
04Nm 30:10 "If a woman living with her husband makes a vow or obligates herself by a pledge under oath
04Nm 30:11 and her husband hears about it but says nothing to her and does not forbid her, then all her vows or the pledges by which she obligated herself will stand.
04Nm 30:12 But if her husband nullifies them when he hears about them, then none of the vows or pledges that came from her lips will stand. Her husband has nullified them, and the LORD will release her.
04Nm 30:13 Her husband may confirm or nullify any vow she makes or any sworn pledge to deny herself.
04Nm 30:14 But if her husband says nothing to her about it from day to day, then he confirms all her vows or the pledges binding on her. He confirms them by saying nothing to her when he hears about them.
04Nm 30:15 If, however, he nullifies them some time after he hears about them, then he is responsible for her guilt."
04Nm 30:16 These are the regulations the LORD gave Moses concerning relationships between a man and his wife, and between a father and his young daughter still living in his house.
04Nm 31:1 The LORD said to Moses,
04Nm 31:2 "Take vengeance on the Midianites for the Israelites. After that, you will be gathered to your people."
04Nm 31:3 So Moses said to the people, "Arm some of your men to go to war against the Midianites and to carry out the LORD'S vengeance on them.
04Nm 31:4 Send into battle a thousand men from each of the tribes of Israel."
04Nm 31:5 So twelve thousand men armed for battle, a thousand from each tribe, were supplied from the clans of Israel.
04Nm 31:6 Moses sent them into battle, a thousand from each tribe, along with Phinehas son of Eleazar, the priest, who took with him articles from the sanctuary and the trumpets for signaling.
04Nm 31:7 They fought against Midian, as the LORD commanded Moses, and killed every man.
04Nm 31:8 Among their victims were Evi, Rekem, Zur, Hur and Reba--the five kings of Midian. They also killed Balaam son of Beor with the sword.
04Nm 31:9 The Israelites captured the Midianite women and children and took all the Midianite herds, flocks and goods as plunder.
04Nm 31:10 They burned all the towns where the Midianites had settled, as well as all their camps.
04Nm 31:11 They took all the plunder and spoils, including the people and animals,
04Nm 31:12 and brought the captives, spoils and plunder to Moses and Eleazar the priest and the Israelite assembly at their camp on the plains of Moab, by the Jordan across from Jericho.
04Nm 31:13 Moses, Eleazar the priest and all the leaders of the community went to meet them outside the camp.
04Nm 31:14 Moses was angry with the officers of the army--the commanders of thousands and commanders of hundreds--who returned from the battle.
04Nm 31:15 "Have you allowed all the women to live?" he asked them.
04Nm 31:16 "They were the ones who followed Balaam's advice and were the means of turning the Israelites away from the LORD in what happened at Peor, so that a plague struck the LORD'S people.
04Nm 31:17 Now kill all the boys. And kill every woman who has slept with a man,
04Nm 31:18 but save for yourselves every girl who has never slept with a man.
04Nm 31:19 "All of you who have killed anyone or touched anyone who was killed must stay outside the camp seven days. On the third and seventh days you must purify yourselves and your captives.
04Nm 31:20 Purify every garment as well as everything made of leather, goat hair or wood."
04Nm 31:21 Then Eleazar the priest said to the soldiers who had gone into battle, "This is the requirement of the law that the LORD gave Moses£º
04Nm 31:22 Gold, silver, bronze, iron, tin, lead
04Nm 31:23 and anything else that can withstand fire must be put through the fire, and then it will be clean. But it must also be purified with the water of cleansing. And whatever cannot withstand fire must be put through that water.
04Nm 31:24 On the seventh day wash your clothes and you will be clean. Then you may come into the camp."
04Nm 31:25 The LORD said to Moses,
04Nm 31:26 "You and Eleazar the priest and the family heads of the community are to count all the people and animals that were captured.
04Nm 31:27 Divide the spoils between the soldiers who took part in the battle and the rest of the community.
04Nm 31:28 From the soldiers who fought in the battle, set apart as tribute for the LORD one out of every five hundred, whether persons, cattle, donkeys, sheep or goats.
04Nm 31:29 Take this tribute from their half share and give it to Eleazar the priest as the LORD'S part.
04Nm 31:30 From the Israelites' half, select one out of every fifty, whether persons, cattle, donkeys, sheep, goats or other animals. Give them to the Levites, who are responsible for the care of the LORD'S tabernacle."
04Nm 31:31 So Moses and Eleazar the priest did as the LORD commanded Moses.
04Nm 31:32 The plunder remaining from the spoils that the soldiers took was 675,000 sheep,
04Nm 31:33 72,000 cattle,
04Nm 31:34 61,000 donkeys
04Nm 31:35 and 32,000 women who had never slept with a man.
04Nm 31:36 The half share of those who fought in the battle was£º 337,500 sheep,
04Nm 31:37 of which the tribute for the LORD was 675;
04Nm 31:38 36,000 cattle, of which the tribute for the LORD was 72;
04Nm 31:39 30,500 donkeys, of which the tribute for the LORD was 61;
04Nm 31:40 16,000 people, of which the tribute for the LORD was 32.
04Nm 31:41 Moses gave the tribute to Eleazar the priest as the LORD'S part, as the LORD commanded Moses.
04Nm 31:42 The half belonging to the Israelites, which Moses set apart from that of the fighting men--
04Nm 31:43 the community's half--was 337,500 sheep,
04Nm 31:44 36,000 cattle,
04Nm 31:45 30,500 donkeys
04Nm 31:46 and 16,000 people.
04Nm 31:47 From the Israelites' half, Moses selected one out of every fifty persons and animals, as the LORD commanded him, and gave them to the Levites, who were responsible for the care of the LORD'S tabernacle.
04Nm 31:48 Then the officers who were over the units of the army--the commanders of thousands and commanders of hundreds--went to Moses
04Nm 31:49 and said to him, "Your servants have counted the soldiers under our command, and not one is missing.
04Nm 31:50 So we have brought as an offering to the LORD the gold articles each of us acquired--armlets, bracelets, signet rings, earrings and necklaces--to make atonement for ourselves before the LORD."
04Nm 31:51 Moses and Eleazar the priest accepted from them the gold--all the crafted articles.
04Nm 31:52 All the gold from the commanders of thousands and commanders of hundreds that Moses and Eleazar presented as a gift to the LORD weighed 16,750 shekels.
04Nm 31:53 Each soldier had taken plunder for himself.
04Nm 31:54 Moses and Eleazar the priest accepted the gold from the commanders of thousands and commanders of hundreds and brought it into the Tent of Meeting as a memorial for the Israelites before the LORD.
04Nm 32:1 The Reubenites and Gadites, who had very large herds and flocks, saw that the lands of Jazer and Gilead were suitable for livestock.
04Nm 32:2 So they came to Moses and Eleazar the priest and to the leaders of the community, and said,
04Nm 32:3 "Ataroth, Dibon, Jazer, Nimrah, Heshbon, Elealeh, Sebam, Nebo and Beon--
04Nm 32:4 the land the LORD subdued before the people of Israel--are suitable for livestock, and your servants have livestock.
04Nm 32:5 If we have found favor in your eyes," they said, "let this land be given to your servants as our possession. Do not make us cross the Jordan."
04Nm 32:6 Moses said to the Gadites and Reubenites, "Shall your countrymen go to war while you sit here?
04Nm 32:7 Why do you discourage the Israelites from going over into the land the LORD has given them?
04Nm 32:8 This is what your fathers did when I sent them from Kadesh Barnea to look over the land.
04Nm 32:9 After they went up to the Valley of Eshcol and viewed the land, they discouraged the Israelites from entering the land the LORD had given them.
04Nm 32:10 The LORD'S anger was aroused that day and he swore this oath£º
04Nm 32:11 'Because they have not followed me wholeheartedly, not one of the men twenty years old or more who came up out of Egypt will see the land I promised on oath to Abraham, Isaac and Jacob--
04Nm 32:12 not one except Caleb son of Jephunneh the Kenizzite and Joshua son of Nun, for they followed the LORD wholeheartedly.'
04Nm 32:13 The LORD'S anger burned against Israel and he made them wander in the desert forty years, until the whole generation of those who had done evil in his sight was gone.
04Nm 32:14 "And here you are, a brood of sinners, standing in the place of your fathers and making the LORD even more angry with Israel.
04Nm 32:15 If you turn away from following him, he will again leave all this people in the desert, and you will be the cause of their destruction."
04Nm 32:16 Then they came up to him and said, "We would like to build pens here for our livestock and cities for our women and children.
04Nm 32:17 But we are ready to arm ourselves and go ahead of the Israelites until we have brought them to their place. Meanwhile our women and children will live in fortified cities, for protection from the inhabitants of the land.
04Nm 32:18 We will not return to our homes until every Israelite has received his inheritance.
04Nm 32:19 We will not receive any inheritance with them on the other side of the Jordan, because our inheritance has come to us on the east side of the Jordan."
04Nm 32:20 Then Moses said to them, "If you will do this--if you will arm yourselves before the LORD for battle,
04Nm 32:21 and if all of you will go armed over the Jordan before the LORD until he has driven his enemies out before him--
04Nm 32:22 then when the land is subdued before the LORD, you may return and be free from your obligation to the LORD and to Israel. And this land will be your possession before the LORD.
04Nm 32:23 "But if you fail to do this, you will be sinning against the LORD; and you may be sure that your sin will find you out.
04Nm 32:24 Build cities for your women and children, and pens for your flocks, but do what you have promised."
04Nm 32:25 The Gadites and Reubenites said to Moses, "We your servants will do as our lord commands.
04Nm 32:26 Our children and wives, our flocks and herds will remain here in the cities of Gilead.
04Nm 32:27 But your servants, every man armed for battle, will cross over to fight before the LORD, just as our lord says."
04Nm 32:28 Then Moses gave orders about them to Eleazar the priest and Joshua son of Nun and to the family heads of the Israelite tribes.
04Nm 32:29 He said to them, "If the Gadites and Reubenites, every man armed for battle, cross over the Jordan with you before the LORD, then when the land is subdued before you, give them the land of Gilead as their possession.
04Nm 32:30 But if they do not cross over with you armed, they must accept their possession with you in Canaan."
04Nm 32:31 The Gadites and Reubenites answered, "Your servants will do what the LORD has said.
04Nm 32:32 We will cross over before the LORD into Canaan armed, but the property we inherit will be on this side of the Jordan."
04Nm 32:33 Then Moses gave to the Gadites, the Reubenites and the half-tribe of Manasseh son of Joseph the kingdom of Sihon king of the Amorites and the kingdom of Og king of Bashan--the whole land with its cities and the territory around them.
04Nm 32:34 The Gadites built up Dibon, Ataroth, Aroer,
04Nm 32:35 Atroth Shophan, Jazer, Jogbehah,
04Nm 32:36 Beth Nimrah and Beth Haran as fortified cities, and built pens for their flocks.
04Nm 32:37 And the Reubenites rebuilt Heshbon, Elealeh and Kiriathaim,
04Nm 32:38 as well as Nebo and Baal Meon (these names were changed) and Sibmah. They gave names to the cities they rebuilt.
04Nm 32:39 The descendants of Makir son of Manasseh went to Gilead, captured it and drove out the Amorites who were there.
04Nm 32:40 So Moses gave Gilead to the Makirites, the descendants of Manasseh, and they settled there.
04Nm 32:41 Jair, a descendant of Manasseh, captured their settlements and called them Havvoth Jair.
04Nm 32:42 And Nobah captured Kenath and its surrounding settlements and called it Nobah after himself.
